00:24:55.030 --> 00:24:57.430
THE BOOK OF ISAIAH

00:25:01.670 --> 00:25:05.870
And it came to pass, in the days of Ahaz,

00:25:06.170 --> 00:25:09.950
the son of Jotham, the son of Uzziah,

00:25:10.150 --> 00:25:12.970
king of Judah, that Rezin,

00:25:13.470 --> 00:25:16.350
the king of Syria, and Pekah,

00:25:16.550 --> 00:25:19.870
the son of Ramaliah, king of Israel,

00:25:20.170 --> 00:25:24.790
went up toward Jerusalem to war against it,

00:25:24.790 --> 00:25:27.950
but could not prevail against it.

00:25:28.430 --> 00:25:32.090
And it was told the house of David, saying,

00:25:32.510 --> 00:25:35.450
Syria is confederate with Ephraim,

00:25:35.750 --> 00:25:37.590
and his heart was moved,

00:25:38.010 --> 00:25:39.390
and the heart of his people,

00:25:39.690 --> 00:25:43.090
as the trees of the wood are moved with the wind.

00:25:43.770 --> 00:25:46.130
Then said the Lord unto Isaiah,

00:25:46.430 --> 00:25:49.530
Go forth now to meet Ahaz,

00:25:49.650 --> 00:25:53.090
thou, and Shear-deshab thy son.

00:25:53.090 --> 00:25:56.550
At the end of the conduit of the upper pool,

00:25:57.050 --> 00:25:59.790
in the highway of the fuller's field.

00:26:00.690 --> 00:26:02.370
And say unto him,

00:26:03.010 --> 00:26:05.290
Take heed, and be quiet,

00:26:05.690 --> 00:26:08.110
fear not neither be faint-hearted,

00:26:08.750 --> 00:26:12.390
for the two tales of these smoking-fire brands,

00:26:12.850 --> 00:26:16.370
for the fierce anger of Rezin with Syria,

00:26:17.050 --> 00:26:19.250
and of the son of Ramaliah.

00:26:19.970 --> 00:26:25.110
Because Syria, Ephraim, and the son of Ramaliah,

00:26:25.430 --> 00:26:28.570
have taken evil counsel against thee,

00:26:28.990 --> 00:26:34.130
saying, Let us go up against Judah and vex it,

00:26:34.430 --> 00:26:37.850
and let us make a breach therein for us,

00:26:38.290 --> 00:26:40.910
and set a king in the midst of it,

00:26:41.130 --> 00:26:43.690
even the son of Tabeel.

00:26:44.290 --> 00:26:46.270
Thus saith the Lord God,

00:26:46.270 --> 00:26:50.910
It shall not stand, neither shall it come to pass,

00:26:51.250 --> 00:26:53.790
for the head of Syria is Damascus,

00:26:54.570 --> 00:26:57.310
and the head of Damascus is Rezin,

00:26:57.770 --> 00:27:04.110
and within three score and five years shall Ephraim be broken,

00:27:04.650 --> 00:27:06.590
that it be not a people.

00:27:07.070 --> 00:27:10.070
And the head of Ephraim is Samaria,

00:27:10.350 --> 00:27:14.750
and the head of Samaria is Ramaliah's son.

00:27:15.170 --> 00:27:21.110
If ye will not believe, surely ye shall not be established.

00:27:22.210 --> 00:27:26.950
Moreover, the Lord spake again unto Ahaz, saying,

00:27:27.730 --> 00:27:30.870
Ask thee a sign of the Lord thy God,

00:27:30.990 --> 00:27:36.030
ask it either in the depth or in the height above.

00:27:36.410 --> 00:27:42.230
But Ahaz said, I will not ask, neither will I tempt the Lord.

00:27:42.230 --> 00:27:46.970
And he said, Hear ye now, O house of David,

00:27:47.610 --> 00:27:51.650
is it a small thing for you to weary men,

00:27:52.230 --> 00:27:55.250
but will ye weary my God also?

00:27:55.810 --> 00:27:59.670
Therefore the Lord himself shall give you a sign,

00:28:00.030 --> 00:28:05.190
behold, a virgin shall conceive and bear a son,

00:28:05.630 --> 00:28:08.390
and shall call his name Immanuel.

00:28:09.110 --> 00:28:11.470
Butter and honey shall he eat,

00:28:12.110 --> 00:28:17.710
that he may know to refuse the evil and choose the good.

00:28:18.430 --> 00:28:24.030
For before the child shall know to refuse the evil and choose the good,

00:28:24.490 --> 00:28:30.210
the land that thou abhorrest shall be forsaken of both her kings.

00:28:30.850 --> 00:28:34.750
The Lord shall bring upon thee and upon thy people

00:28:34.750 --> 00:28:40.450
and upon thy father's house days that have not come,

00:28:40.790 --> 00:28:46.390
from the day that Ephraim departed from Judah, even the king of Assyria.

00:28:46.570 --> 00:28:51.890
And it shall come to pass in that day that the Lord shall hiss

00:28:51.890 --> 00:28:57.690
for the fly that is in the uttermost part of the rivers of Egypt,

00:28:57.910 --> 00:29:01.950
and for the bee that is in the land of Assyria.

00:29:01.950 --> 00:29:06.250
And they shall come and shall rest, all of them,

00:29:06.570 --> 00:29:10.610
in the desolate valleys and in the holes of the rocks,

00:29:10.770 --> 00:29:15.110
and upon all thorns and upon all bushes.

00:29:15.650 --> 00:29:22.470
In the same day shall the Lord save with a razor that is hired,

00:29:22.830 --> 00:29:26.930
namely, by them beyond the river, by the king of Assyria,

00:29:27.330 --> 00:29:29.810
the head and the hair of the feet.

00:29:29.810 --> 00:29:36.330
And it shall also consume the beard, and it shall come to pass in that day

00:29:36.330 --> 00:29:40.430
that a man shall nourish a young cow and two sheep.

00:29:40.770 --> 00:29:46.410
And it shall come to pass for the abundance of milk that they shall give,

00:29:46.950 --> 00:29:49.190
he shall eat butter.

00:29:49.770 --> 00:29:55.390
For butter and honey shall everyone eat that is left in the land.

00:29:55.390 --> 00:30:00.150
And it shall come to pass in that day that every place shall be

00:30:00.430 --> 00:30:05.710
where there were a thousand vines at a thousand silverlings.

00:30:06.090 --> 00:30:09.470
It shall even be for briars and thorns.

00:30:09.970 --> 00:30:14.090
With arrows and with bows shall men come thither,

00:30:14.290 --> 00:30:18.670
because all the land shall become briars and thorns.

00:30:19.130 --> 00:30:23.490
And on all the hills that shall be digged with the matak,

00:30:23.490 --> 00:30:27.630
there shall not come neither the fear of briars and thorns,

00:30:28.070 --> 00:30:31.410
but it shall be for the sending forth of oxen

00:30:31.410 --> 00:30:33.950
and for the treading of lesser cattle.

00:30:36.310 --> 00:30:39.310
Moreover, the Lord said unto me,

00:30:39.430 --> 00:30:46.070
Take thee a great roll, and write it in with a man's pen,

00:30:46.350 --> 00:30:50.930
concerning Maher shal al-Hashbaz.

00:30:50.930 --> 00:30:56.490
And I took unto me faithful witnesses to record Uriah the priest,

00:30:56.810 --> 00:31:01.610
and Zechariah the son of Jebur Recahiah.

00:31:02.330 --> 00:31:07.550
And I went unto the prophetess, and she conceived, and bare a son.

00:31:08.150 --> 00:31:10.470
Then said the Lord to me,

00:31:10.930 --> 00:31:15.170
Call his name, Maher shal al-Hashbaz.

00:31:16.470 --> 00:31:19.730
For before the child shall have knowledge to cry,

00:31:19.730 --> 00:31:26.770
my father and my mother, the riches of Damascus and the spoil of Samaria,

00:31:26.930 --> 00:31:30.610
shall be taken away before the king of Assyria.

00:31:31.110 --> 00:31:34.990
The Lord spake also unto me again, saying,

00:31:35.290 --> 00:31:41.990
For as much as this people refuseth the waters of Shiloh that go softly,

00:31:42.710 --> 00:31:46.710
and rejoice and resin in Remaliah's son,

00:31:46.710 --> 00:31:53.310
now therefore behold the Lord bringeth up upon them the waters of the river,

00:31:53.310 --> 00:31:58.710
strong and many, even the king of Assyria and all his glory,

00:31:58.910 --> 00:32:05.350
and he shall come up over all his channels, and go over all his banks.

00:32:05.850 --> 00:32:10.870
And he shall pass through Judah, he shall overflow and go over,

00:32:11.250 --> 00:32:16.310
he shall reach even to the neck, and the stretching out of his wings,

00:32:16.310 --> 00:32:21.430
shall fill the breadth of thy land, O Immanuel.

00:32:23.250 --> 00:32:28.730
Associate yourselves, O ye people, and ye shall be broken in pieces,

00:32:29.070 --> 00:32:33.930
and give ear, all ye of far countries, gird yourselves,

00:32:34.230 --> 00:32:36.970
and ye shall be broken in pieces.

00:32:37.290 --> 00:32:41.950
Gird yourselves, and ye shall be broken in pieces.

00:32:42.430 --> 00:32:45.610
Take counsel together, and it shall come to naught.

00:32:45.610 --> 00:32:51.510
Speak the word, and it shall not stand, for God is with us.

00:32:51.890 --> 00:32:55.650
For the Lord spake thus to me with a strong hand,

00:32:56.110 --> 00:33:01.350
and instructed me that I should not walk in the way of this people,

00:33:02.430 --> 00:33:09.870
say ye not a confederacy to all them to whom this people shall say a confederacy.

00:33:10.290 --> 00:33:14.770
Neither fear ye their fear, nor be afraid.

00:33:14.770 --> 00:33:22.890
Sanctify the Lord of Hosts himself, and let him be your fear, and let him be your dread.

00:33:23.650 --> 00:33:29.550
And he shall be for a sanctuary, but for a stone of stumbling,

00:33:29.910 --> 00:33:34.690
and for a rock of offense to both the houses of Israel,

00:33:35.070 --> 00:33:41.290
for a djinn, and for a snare to the inhabitants of Jerusalem.

00:33:42.130 --> 00:33:48.870
And many among them shall stumble, and fall, and be broken, and be snared, and be taken.

00:33:49.430 --> 00:33:54.010
Bind up the testimony, seal the law among my disciples,

00:33:54.370 --> 00:34:00.250
and I will wait upon the Lord that hideth his face from the house of Jacob,

00:34:00.370 --> 00:34:02.290
and I will look for him.

00:34:02.410 --> 00:34:06.410
Behold, I and the children whom the Lord hath given me

00:34:06.410 --> 00:34:16.310
are for signs and for wonders in Israel from the Lord of Hosts which dwelleth in Mount Zion.

00:34:16.950 --> 00:34:23.270
And when they shall say unto you, seek unto them that have familiar spirits,

00:34:23.750 --> 00:34:26.890
and unto wizards that peep, and that mutter,

00:34:27.530 --> 00:34:32.490
should not a people seek unto their God for the living to the dead,

00:34:32.490 --> 00:34:38.290
to the law and to the testimony, if they speak not according to this word,

00:34:38.510 --> 00:34:41.490
it is because there is no light in them.

00:34:41.810 --> 00:34:46.550
And they shall pass through it, hardly bested and hungry,

00:34:46.770 --> 00:34:50.750
and it shall come to pass, that when they shall be hungry,

00:34:51.070 --> 00:34:55.150
they shall fret themselves, and curse their king and their God,

00:34:55.350 --> 00:34:59.330
and look upward, and they shall look onto the earth,

00:34:59.330 --> 00:35:04.570
and behold, trouble and darkness, demnis of anguish,

00:35:04.910 --> 00:35:07.290
and they shall be driven to darkness.

00:35:08.510 --> 00:35:16.230
Nevertheless, the demnis shall not be such as was in her vexation,

00:35:16.690 --> 00:35:21.510
when at the first he lightly afflicted the land of Zebulon,

00:35:21.690 --> 00:35:23.910
and the land of Nephtali,

00:35:23.910 --> 00:35:28.070
and afterward did more grievously afflict her,

00:35:28.270 --> 00:35:33.250
by the way of the sea, beyond Jordan in Galilee of the nations.

00:35:33.810 --> 00:35:38.550
The people that walked in darkness have seen a great light.

00:35:38.950 --> 00:35:42.490
They that dwell in the land of the shadow of death,

00:35:42.650 --> 00:35:45.250
upon them hath the light shined.

00:35:45.510 --> 00:35:50.970
Thou hast multiplied the nation, and not increased the joy.

00:35:50.970 --> 00:35:55.270
They joy before thee according to the joy in harvest,

00:35:55.750 --> 00:35:59.450
and as men rejoice when they divide the spoil.

00:36:00.050 --> 00:36:02.750
For thou hast broken the yoke of his burden,

00:36:03.210 --> 00:36:07.830
and the staff of his shoulder, the rod of his oppressor,

00:36:07.950 --> 00:36:10.030
as in the day of Midian.

00:36:10.630 --> 00:36:14.610
For every battle of the warrior is with confused noise,

00:36:14.930 --> 00:36:17.230
and garments rolled in blood.

00:36:17.230 --> 00:36:23.530
But this shall be with burning and fuel of fire,

00:36:23.790 --> 00:36:30.090
for unto us a child is born, unto us a son is given,

00:36:30.370 --> 00:36:33.770
and the government shall be upon his shoulder,

00:36:34.130 --> 00:36:37.570
and his name shall be called Wonderful,

00:36:38.290 --> 00:36:40.610
Counselor, the Mighty God,

00:36:41.210 --> 00:36:45.550
the Everlasting Father, the Prince of Peace.

00:36:46.050 --> 00:36:49.310
Of the increase of his government and peace,

00:36:49.630 --> 00:36:53.570
there shall be no end upon the throne of David,

00:36:53.850 --> 00:36:57.310
and upon his kingdom to order it,

00:36:57.350 --> 00:37:00.750
and to establish it with judgment and with justice,

00:37:01.110 --> 00:37:03.530
from henceforth even forever.

00:37:04.050 --> 00:37:08.290
The zeal of the Lord of hosts will perform this.

00:37:08.790 --> 00:37:11.830
The Lord sent his word into Jacob,

00:37:12.230 --> 00:37:14.750
and it hath lighted upon Israel,

00:37:14.750 --> 00:37:18.850
and all the people shall know, even Ephraim,

00:37:19.250 --> 00:37:21.450
and the inhabitant of Samaria,

00:37:21.870 --> 00:37:24.990
that say in the pride and stoutness of heart,

00:37:25.430 --> 00:37:29.910
the bricks are fallen down, but we will build with hewn stones,

00:37:30.290 --> 00:37:35.190
the sycamores are cut down, but we will change them into cedars.

00:37:35.490 --> 00:37:41.090
Therefore, the Lord shall set up the adversaries of resin against him,

00:37:41.510 --> 00:37:43.870
and join his enemies together.

00:37:43.870 --> 00:37:48.350
The Syrians before, and the Philistines behind,

00:37:48.970 --> 00:37:52.290
and they shall devour Israel with open mouth.

00:37:53.170 --> 00:37:57.130
For all this, his anger is not turned away,

00:37:57.310 --> 00:38:00.570
but his hand is stretched out still.

00:38:01.290 --> 00:38:05.770
For the people turneth not unto him that smiteth them,

00:38:05.970 --> 00:38:08.930
neither do they seek the Lord of hosts.

00:38:09.450 --> 00:38:13.630
Therefore, the Lord will cut off from Israel,

00:38:13.630 --> 00:38:18.670
head and tail, branch and rush in one day.

00:38:19.330 --> 00:38:23.410
The ancient and honorable, he is the head,

00:38:23.710 --> 00:38:29.430
and the prophet that teacheth lies, he is the tail.

00:38:30.170 --> 00:38:34.270
For the leaders of this people cause them to err,

00:38:34.830 --> 00:38:38.610
and they that are led of them are destroyed.

00:38:38.930 --> 00:38:42.930
Therefore, the Lord shall have no joy in their young men,

00:38:42.930 --> 00:38:47.270
neither shall have mercy on their fatherless and widows.

00:38:47.790 --> 00:38:51.850
For everyone is in hypocrite and in evildoer,

00:38:52.170 --> 00:38:54.530
and every mouth speaketh folly.

00:38:54.990 --> 00:38:58.810
For all this, his anger is not turned away,

00:38:59.350 --> 00:39:02.710
but his hand is stretched out still.

00:39:03.430 --> 00:39:06.190
For wickedness burneth as the fire,

00:39:06.550 --> 00:39:09.290
it shall devour the briars and thorns,

00:39:09.670 --> 00:39:12.630
and shall kindle in the thickets of the forest,

00:39:12.630 --> 00:39:17.830
and they shall mount up like the lifting up of smoke.

00:39:18.390 --> 00:39:23.850
Through the wrath of the Lord of hosts is the land darkened,

00:39:24.110 --> 00:39:28.110
and the people shall be as the fuel of the fire.

00:39:28.490 --> 00:39:31.470
No man shall spare his brother,

00:39:31.830 --> 00:39:35.930
and he shall snatch on the right hand and be hungry,

00:39:36.110 --> 00:39:38.950
and he shall eat on the left hand,

00:39:38.950 --> 00:39:41.730
and they shall not be satisfied.

00:39:41.730 --> 00:39:46.510
They shall eat every man the flesh of his own arm.

00:39:47.830 --> 00:39:51.410
Manasseh, Ephraim, and Ephraim Manasseh,

00:39:52.130 --> 00:39:55.390
and they together shall be against Judah.

00:39:55.910 --> 00:40:00.310
For all this, his anger is not turned away,

00:40:00.370 --> 00:40:04.550
but his hand is stretched out still.

00:40:48.418 --> 00:40:52.238
Woe unto them that decree unrighteous decrees,

00:40:52.438 --> 00:40:57.338
and that right grievousness which they have prescribed,

00:40:57.678 --> 00:41:00.678
to turn aside the needy from judgment,

00:41:00.758 --> 00:41:04.918
and to take away the right from the poor of my people,

00:41:05.278 --> 00:41:10.698
that widows may be their prey, and that they may rob the fatherless.

00:41:10.698 --> 00:41:14.298
And what will ye do in the day of visitation,

00:41:14.558 --> 00:41:18.638
and in the desolation which shall come from far?

00:41:19.078 --> 00:41:21.178
To whom will ye flee for help?

00:41:21.538 --> 00:41:24.358
And where will ye leave your glory?

00:41:24.778 --> 00:41:28.378
Without me they shall bow down under the prisoners,

00:41:28.558 --> 00:41:32.158
and they shall fall under the slain.

00:41:32.458 --> 00:41:36.458
For all this his anger is not turned away,

00:41:37.098 --> 00:41:40.138
but his hand is stretched out still.

00:41:41.138 --> 00:41:44.318
O Assyrian, the rod of my anger,

00:41:44.798 --> 00:41:48.838
and the staff in their hand of mine indignation,

00:41:49.078 --> 00:41:52.958
I will send him against an hypocritical nation,

00:41:53.258 --> 00:41:58.038
and against the people of my wrath will I give him a charge,

00:41:58.318 --> 00:42:01.738
to take the spoil and to take the prey,

00:42:01.998 --> 00:42:06.058
and to tread them down like the mire of the streets.

00:42:06.058 --> 00:42:11.918
Howbeit he meaneth not so, neither doth his heart think so,

00:42:12.218 --> 00:42:18.658
but it is in his heart to destroy, and cut off nations, not a few.

00:42:19.238 --> 00:42:23.438
For he sayeth, Are not my princes altogether kings?

00:42:23.998 --> 00:42:28.318
Is not Calno as Kar-Kamish?

00:42:28.738 --> 00:42:31.538
Is not Hamath as Arpad?

00:42:31.538 --> 00:42:35.478
Is not Samaria as Damascus?

00:42:36.158 --> 00:42:39.518
As my hand hath found the kingdoms of the idols,

00:42:40.118 --> 00:42:46.458
and whose graven images do excel them of Jerusalem and of Samaria,

00:42:46.878 --> 00:42:51.438
shall I not, as I have done unto Samaria and her idols,

00:42:51.598 --> 00:42:54.658
so do to Jerusalem and her idols?

00:42:55.238 --> 00:42:57.758
Wherefore it shall come to pass,

00:42:57.758 --> 00:43:03.618
that when the Lord hath performed his whole work upon Mount Zion,

00:43:03.998 --> 00:43:08.978
and on Jerusalem, I will punish the fruit of the stout heart

00:43:08.978 --> 00:43:13.818
of the king of Assyria, and the glory of his high looks.

00:43:14.278 --> 00:43:18.578
For he sayeth, By the strength of my hand I have done it,

00:43:18.578 --> 00:43:20.638
and by my wisdom.

00:43:20.918 --> 00:43:25.158
For I am prudent, and I have removed the bonds of the people,

00:43:25.158 --> 00:43:29.238
and have robbed their treasures, and I have put down the inhabitants

00:43:29.238 --> 00:43:31.038
like a valiant man.

00:43:31.898 --> 00:43:37.658
And my hand hath found, as a nest of riches of the people,

00:43:37.958 --> 00:43:43.638
and as one gathereth eggs that are left, have I gathered all the earth.

00:43:44.158 --> 00:43:50.958
And there was none that moved the wing, or opened the mouth, or peeped.

00:43:50.958 --> 00:43:55.298
Shall the axe boast itself against him that heweth therewith,

00:43:55.818 --> 00:44:01.678
or shall the saw magnify itself against him that shaketh it,

00:44:02.258 --> 00:44:07.438
as if the rod should shake itself against them that lift it up,

00:44:07.698 --> 00:44:13.858
or as if the staff should lift up itself as if it were no wood?

00:44:14.278 --> 00:44:20.438
Therefore shall the Lord, the Lord of hosts, send among his fat ones leanness,

00:44:20.438 --> 00:44:26.358
and under his glory he shall kindle a burning, like the burning of a fire.

00:44:26.758 --> 00:44:33.758
And the light of Israel shall be for a fire, and his holy one for a flame.

00:44:33.958 --> 00:44:39.898
And it shall burn and devour his thorns and his briars in one day,

00:44:40.478 --> 00:44:45.618
and shall consume the glory of his forest, and of his fruitful field,

00:44:45.618 --> 00:44:53.358
both soul and body, and they shall be as when a standard bearer fainteth.

00:44:53.838 --> 00:45:00.218
And the rest of the trees of his forest shall be few, that a child may write them.

00:45:01.158 --> 00:45:06.938
And it shall come to pass in that day, that the remnant of Israel,

00:45:07.378 --> 00:45:14.138
and such as are escaped of the house of Jacob, shall no more again stay upon him

00:45:14.138 --> 00:45:21.138
that smote them, but shall stay upon the Lord, the holy one of Israel, in truth.

00:45:21.778 --> 00:45:28.038
The remnant shall return, even the remnant of Jacob, unto the mighty God.

00:45:29.078 --> 00:45:37.318
For thou, thy people Israel, be as the sand of the sea, yet a remnant of them shall return.

00:45:37.678 --> 00:45:43.398
The consumption decreed shall overflow with righteousness.

00:45:43.398 --> 00:45:52.438
For the Lord God of hosts shall make a consumption even determined in the midst of all the land.

00:45:53.098 --> 00:46:00.078
Therefore, thus saith the Lord God of hosts, O my people that dwellest in Zion,

00:46:00.538 --> 00:46:05.218
be not afraid of the Assyrian. He shall smite thee with a rod,

00:46:05.538 --> 00:46:10.178
and shall lift up his staff against thee after the manner of Egypt.

00:46:10.178 --> 00:46:19.738
For yet a very little while, and the indignation shall cease, and mine anger in their destruction.

00:46:20.658 --> 00:46:24.618
And the Lord of hosts shall stir up a scourge for him,

00:46:24.998 --> 00:46:28.778
according to the slaughter of Midian at the rock of Oreb.

00:46:29.378 --> 00:46:36.338
And his rod was upon the sea, so shall he lift it up after the manner of Egypt.

00:46:36.338 --> 00:46:43.698
And it shall come to pass in that day, that his burden shall be taken away from off thy shoulder,

00:46:43.958 --> 00:46:50.678
and his yoke from off thy neck, and the yoke shall be destroyed because of the anointing.

00:46:51.958 --> 00:46:58.398
He is come to Ayathe. He is passed to Megrun.

00:46:58.398 --> 00:47:06.338
At Micmash, he hath laid up his carriages. They are gone over the passage.

00:47:06.658 --> 00:47:11.378
They have taken up their lodging and gibba. Ramah is afraid.

00:47:11.998 --> 00:47:17.938
Kabiah of Saul is fled. Lift up thy voice, O daughter of Gollum.

00:47:18.158 --> 00:47:22.338
Cause it to be heard unto Laish, O poor Anathoth.

00:47:23.338 --> 00:47:30.658
Madmenna is removed. The inhabitants of Gibbim gather themselves to flee.

00:47:31.338 --> 00:47:38.038
As yet shall he remain at Nob that day. He shall shake his hand against the mount

00:47:38.038 --> 00:47:46.198
of the daughter of Zion, the hill of Jerusalem. Behold, the Lord, the Lord of hosts shall lop

00:47:46.198 --> 00:47:55.058
the bough with terror, and the high ones of stature shall be hewn down, and the hearty shall be

00:47:55.058 --> 00:48:03.018
humbled. And he shall cut down the thickets of the forest with iron, and Lebanon shall be a mighty one.

00:48:03.618 --> 00:48:12.898
And there shall come forth a rod out of the stem of Jesse, and a branch shall grow out

00:48:12.898 --> 00:48:21.218
of his roots. And the spirit of the Lord shall rest upon him, the spirit of wisdom and understanding,

00:48:21.398 --> 00:48:28.998
the spirit of counsel and might, the spirit of knowledge and of the fear of the Lord,

00:48:29.458 --> 00:48:35.018
and shall make him of quick understanding in the fear of the Lord. And he shall not judge

00:48:35.018 --> 00:48:42.038
after the sight of his eyes, neither reprove after the hearing of his ears, but with righteousness

00:48:42.038 --> 00:48:49.318
shall he judge the poor and reprove with equity for the meek of the earth. And he shall smite the

00:48:49.318 --> 00:48:56.578
earth with the rod of his mouth, and with the breath of his lips shall he slay the wicked.

00:48:57.358 --> 00:49:04.418
And righteousness shall be the girdle of his loins, and faithfulness the girdle of his reins.

00:49:04.938 --> 00:49:11.398
The wolf also shall dwell with the lamb, and the leopard shall lie down with the kid and the calf

00:49:11.398 --> 00:49:21.178
and the lion and the fatling together, and a little child shall lead them. And the cow and the bear

00:49:21.178 --> 00:49:28.318
shall feed, their young ones shall lie down together, and the lion shall eat straw like the ox.

00:49:29.058 --> 00:49:41.378
And the suckling child shall play on the hole, and the asp and the weaned child shall put his hand on

00:50:11.378 --> 00:50:18.218
to recover the remnant of his people, which shall be left from Assyria and from Egypt

00:50:18.218 --> 00:50:26.158
and from Pathros and from Cush and from Elam and from Shinar and from Hamath

00:50:26.158 --> 00:50:33.098
and from the islands of the sea. And he shall set up an ensign for the nations,

00:50:33.538 --> 00:50:39.878
and shall assemble the outcasts of Israel, and gather together the dispersed of Judah

00:50:39.878 --> 00:50:46.858
from the four corners of the earth. The envy also of Ephraim shall depart,

00:50:47.338 --> 00:50:54.078
and the adversaries of Judah shall be cut off. Ephraim shall not envy Judah, and Judah

00:50:54.078 --> 00:51:01.838
shall not vex Ephraim. But they shall fly upon the shoulders of the Philistines toward the west.

00:51:02.178 --> 00:51:08.458
They shall spoil them of the east together. They shall lay their hands upon Edom and Moab

00:51:08.458 --> 00:51:14.318
and the children of Ammon shall obey them, and the Lord shall utterly destroy the tongue

00:51:14.318 --> 00:51:20.958
of the Egyptian sea. And with his mighty wind shall he shake his hand over the river,

00:51:21.278 --> 00:51:29.058
and shall smite it in the seven streams, and make men go over Dry Shad. And there shall be

00:51:29.058 --> 00:51:36.898
an highway for the remnant of his people, which shall be left from Assyria, like as it was to

00:51:36.898 --> 00:51:46.558
Israel in the day that he came up out of the land of Egypt. And in that day thou

00:51:46.558 --> 00:51:55.298
shalt say, O Lord, I will praise thee. Though thou wast angry with me, thine anger is turned away,

00:51:55.678 --> 00:52:03.578
and thou comfortest me. Behold, God is my salvation. I will trust and not be afraid,

00:52:03.578 --> 00:52:12.618
for the Lord Jehovah is my strength and my song. He also is become my salvation. Therefore, with

00:52:12.618 --> 00:52:19.758
joy shall ye draw water out of the wells of salvation, and in that day shall ye praise the

00:52:19.758 --> 00:52:28.718
Lord. Call upon his name. Declare his doings among the people. Make mention that his name is exalted.

00:52:28.718 --> 00:52:37.658
Sing unto the Lord, for he hath done excellent things. This is known in all the earth. Cry out

00:52:37.658 --> 00:52:44.858
and shout thou, inhabitant of Zion, for great is the Holy One of Israel in the midst of thee.

00:53:08.363 --> 00:53:28.003
13. The burden of Babylon which Isaiah the son of Amos did see. Lift ye up a banner upon

00:53:28.003 --> 00:53:33.723
the high mountain, exalt the voice unto them, shake the hand that they may go into the gates

00:53:33.723 --> 00:53:39.843
of the nobles. I have commanded my sanctified ones, I have also called my mighty ones for my

00:53:39.843 --> 00:53:45.763
anger, even them that rejoice in my highness. The noise of a multitude in the mountains,

00:53:46.063 --> 00:53:51.003
like as of a great people, a tumultuous noise of the kingdoms and nations gathered together,

00:53:51.003 --> 00:53:57.423
the Lord of hosts must rid the host of the battle. They come from a far country,

00:53:57.563 --> 00:54:02.963
from the end of heaven, even the Lord and the weapons of his indignation, to destroy the whole

00:54:02.963 --> 00:54:10.443
land. How ye for the day of the Lord is at hand, it shall come as a destruction from the Almighty.

00:54:11.543 --> 00:54:17.963
Therefore shall all hands be faint, and every man's heart shall melt, and they shall be afraid,

00:54:17.963 --> 00:54:23.243
pains and sorrows shall take hold of them, they shall be in pain as a woman that travelleth,

00:54:23.563 --> 00:54:30.923
they shall be amazed one at another, their faces shall be as flames. Behold the day of the Lord

00:54:30.923 --> 00:54:37.303
cometh, cruel both with wrath and fierce anger, to lay the lame desolate, he shall destroy the

00:54:37.303 --> 00:54:43.163
sinners thereof out of it. For the stars of heaven and the constellations thereof shall not

00:54:43.163 --> 00:54:47.943
give their light, the sun shall be darkened in his going forth, and the moon shall not cause her

00:54:47.943 --> 00:54:53.903
light to shine. And I will punish the world for their evil, and the wicked for their iniquity,

00:54:54.123 --> 00:54:59.923
and I will cause the arrogance of the proud to cease, and will lay low the haughtiness of the

00:54:59.923 --> 00:55:07.223
terrible. I will make a man more precious than fine gold, even a man than the golden wedge of

00:55:07.223 --> 00:55:13.303
ophir. Therefore I will shake the heavens, and the earth shall remove out of her place,

00:55:13.303 --> 00:55:19.443
in the wrath of the Lord of hosts, and in the day of his fierce anger. And it shall be as the

00:55:19.443 --> 00:55:25.463
chaste roe, and as a sheep that no man taketh up, they shall every man turn to his own people,

00:55:25.863 --> 00:55:31.863
and flee every one into his own land. Every one that is found shall be thrust through,

00:55:32.223 --> 00:55:38.083
and every one that is joined unto them shall fall by the sword. Their children also shall be dashed

00:55:38.083 --> 00:55:45.323
to pieces before their eyes. Their houses shall be spoiled, and their wives ravished. Behold,

00:55:45.403 --> 00:55:51.183
I will stir up the meads against them, which shall not regard silver, and as for gold they

00:55:51.183 --> 00:55:57.723
shall not delight in it. Their bows also shall dash the young men to pieces. They shall have

00:55:57.723 --> 00:56:05.043
no pity on the fruit of the womb. Their eyes shall not spare children. And Babylon, the glory of

00:56:05.043 --> 00:56:10.903
kingdoms, the beauty of the Chaldees, excellency, shall be as when God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah.

00:56:12.383 --> 00:56:18.183
It shall never be inhabited, neither shall it be dwelt in from generation to generation,

00:56:18.643 --> 00:56:23.563
neither shall the Arabian pitch-tent there, neither shall the shepherds make their fold there.

00:56:24.443 --> 00:56:29.203
But wild beasts of the desert shall lie there, and their houses shall be full of doe-full

00:56:29.203 --> 00:56:35.903
creatures, and owls shall dwell there, and satires shall dance there. And the wild beasts

00:56:35.903 --> 00:56:40.823
of the islands shall cry in their desolate houses, and dragons in their pleasant palaces,

00:56:41.183 --> 00:56:45.423
and her time is near to come, and her days shall not be prolonged.

00:56:47.423 --> 00:56:53.283
For the Lord will have mercy on Jacob, and will yet choose Israel,

00:56:53.703 --> 00:56:58.203
and set them in their own land, and the strangers shall be joined with them,

00:56:58.203 --> 00:57:03.563
and they shall cleave to the house of Jacob. And the people shall take them, and bring them

00:57:03.563 --> 00:57:09.103
to their place, and the house of Israel shall possess them in the land of the Lord for servants

00:57:09.103 --> 00:57:15.123
and handmaids, and they shall take them captives, whose captives they were, and they shall rule over

00:57:15.123 --> 00:57:20.743
their oppressors. And it shall come to pass in the day that the Lord shall give them rest from thy

00:57:20.743 --> 00:57:25.563
sorrow, and from thy fear, and from the hard bondage wherein thou wast made to serve,

00:57:26.463 --> 00:57:30.583
that thou shalt take up this proverb against the king of Babylon, and say,

00:57:31.163 --> 00:57:37.443
How hath the oppressor ceased, the Golan city ceased? The Lord hath broken the staff of the

00:57:37.443 --> 00:57:43.883
wicked, and the scepter of the rulers. He who smote the people in wrath with a continual stroke,

00:57:44.243 --> 00:57:51.203
he that ruled the nations in anger is persecuted, and none hindereth. The whole earth is at rest,

00:57:51.203 --> 00:57:57.523
and is quiet. They break forth into singing. Yea, the fir trees rejoice at thee, and the

00:57:57.523 --> 00:58:02.743
cedars of Lebanon, saying, Since thou art laid down, no feller has come up against us.

00:58:03.723 --> 00:58:10.063
Hell from beneath is moved for thee to meet thee at thy coming. It stirreth up the dead for thee,

00:58:10.323 --> 00:58:15.783
even all the chief ones of the earth. It hath raised up from their thrones all the kings of

00:58:15.783 --> 00:58:23.603
the nations. All they shall speak, and say unto thee, Art thou also become weak as we? Art thou

00:58:23.603 --> 00:58:31.483
become like unto us? Thy pomp is brought down to the grave, and the noise of thy vials, the worm

00:58:31.483 --> 00:58:37.923
is spread under thee, and the worms cover thee. How art thou fallen from heaven, O Lucifer,

00:58:38.223 --> 00:58:45.183
son of the morning? How art thou cut down to the ground, which doth weaken the nations? For thou

00:58:45.183 --> 00:58:50.543
hast said in thine heart, I will ascend into heaven, I will exalt my throne above the stars

00:58:50.543 --> 00:58:56.863
of God, I will sit also upon the mount of the congregation, in the sides of the north. I will

00:58:56.863 --> 00:59:03.643
ascend above the heights of the clouds, I will be like the Most High. Yet thou shalt be brought down

00:59:03.643 --> 00:59:09.903
to hell, to the sides of the pit. They that see thee shall narrowly look upon thee, and consider

00:59:09.903 --> 00:59:18.343
thee same. Is this the man that made the earth to tremble, that to shake kingdoms, that made the

00:59:18.343 --> 00:59:23.623
world as a wilderness, and destroyed the cities thereof, that opened not the house of his prisoners?

00:59:24.463 --> 00:59:32.223
All the kings of the nations, even all of them, lie in glory, every one in his own house. But thou

00:59:32.223 --> 00:59:38.703
art cast out of thy grave like an abominable branch, and as the raiment of those that are slain,

00:59:38.703 --> 00:59:45.063
thrust through with a sword, that go down to the stones of the pit, as a carcass trodden under feet.

00:59:46.243 --> 00:59:51.843
Thou shalt not be joined with them in burial, because thou hast destroyed thy land, and slain

00:59:51.843 --> 00:59:58.823
thy people. The seed of evildoers shall never be renowned. Prepare slaughter for his children,

00:59:59.003 --> 01:00:04.643
for the iniquity of their fathers, that they do not rise, nor possess the land, nor fill the face

01:00:04.643 --> 01:00:10.103
of the world with cities. For I will rise up against them, saith the Lord of hosts, and cut off

01:00:10.103 --> 01:00:16.583
from Babylon the name, and remnant, and son, and nephew, saith the Lord. I will also make it a

01:00:16.583 --> 01:00:21.803
possession for the bitter and pools of water, and I will sweep it with the besom of destruction,

01:00:21.983 --> 01:00:28.703
saith the Lord of hosts. The Lord of hosts hath sworn, saying, Surely, as I have thought, so shall

01:00:28.703 --> 01:00:36.163
come to pass, and as I have purposed, so shall it stand, that I will break the Assyrian in my land,

01:00:36.443 --> 01:00:42.163
and upon my mountains tread him under foot, then shall his yoke depart from off them, and his burden

01:00:42.163 --> 01:00:47.043
depart from off their shoulders. This is the purpose that is purposed upon the whole earth,

01:00:47.443 --> 01:00:54.003
and this is the hand that is stretched out upon all the nations. For the Lord of hosts hath purposed,

01:00:54.003 --> 01:01:00.203
who shall disannul it, and his hand is stretched out, and who shall turn it back? In the year that

01:01:00.203 --> 01:01:07.723
King Ahaz died was this burden. Rejoice not thou, whole Palestina, because the rod of him that

01:01:07.723 --> 01:01:13.143
smote thee is broken, for out of the serpent's root shall come forth a cockatrice, and his fruit

01:01:13.143 --> 01:01:19.903
shall be a fiery flying serpent. And the firstborn of the poor shall feed, and the needy shall lie

01:01:19.903 --> 01:01:25.643
down in safety, and I will kill thy root with famine, and he shall slay thy remnant. How,

01:01:25.823 --> 01:01:32.923
O gate, cry, O city, thou whole Palestina art dissolved, for there shall come from the north

01:01:32.923 --> 01:01:39.863
a smoke, and none shall be alone in his appointed times. What shall one then answer the messengers

01:01:39.863 --> 01:01:45.783
of the nation, that the Lord hath founded Zion, and the poor of his people shall trust in it?

01:01:47.523 --> 01:01:55.983
The burden of Moab. Because in the night, R of Moab is laid waste, and brought to

01:01:55.983 --> 01:02:03.663
silence. Because in the night, Kur of Moab is laid waste, and brought to silence. He is gone up to

01:02:03.663 --> 01:02:10.923
Bajith, and to dive on, the high places to weep. Moab shall howl over Nebo, and over Mediba. On all

01:02:10.923 --> 01:02:16.703
our heads shall be baldness, and every beard cut off. In their streets they shall gird themselves

01:02:16.703 --> 01:02:22.263
with sackcloth. On the tops of their houses, and in their streets, every one shall howl, weeping

01:02:22.263 --> 01:02:29.123
abundantly. And Heshbon shall cry, and Elieli. Their voice shall be heard, even unto Jehaz.

01:02:29.483 --> 01:02:35.603
Therefore the armed soldiers of Moab shall cry out. His life shall be grievous unto him. My heart

01:02:35.603 --> 01:02:42.863
shall cry out for Moab. His fugitives shall flee unto Zohar, an heifer of three years old. For by

01:02:42.863 --> 01:02:48.383
the mounting up of Luhith, with weeping shall they go it up. For in the way of Horanaim they

01:02:48.383 --> 01:02:54.243
shall raise up a cry of destruction. For the waters of Nimrum shall be desolate. For the

01:02:54.243 --> 01:03:01.203
hay is withered away, and the grass faileth. There is no green thing. Therefore the abundance

01:03:01.203 --> 01:03:06.103
they have gotten, and that which they have laid up, shall they carry away to the brook of the

01:03:06.103 --> 01:03:12.963
willows. For the cry has gone round about the borders of Moab, and the howling thereof unto

01:03:12.963 --> 01:03:20.543
Eglem, and the howling thereof unto Birlim. For the waters of Daimon shall be full of blood. For I

01:03:20.543 --> 01:03:27.443
will bring more upon Daimon, lions upon him that escapeth of Moab, and upon the remnant of the land.

01:04:11.961 --> 01:04:33.141
Senyi, the lamb, to the ruler of the land, from Sila to the wilderness, unto the mount of the daughter of Zion. For it shall be that as a wandering bird cast out of the nest, so the daughters of Moab shall be at the fords of Arnon.

01:04:33.141 --> 01:04:47.521
Take counsel. Execute judgment. Make thy shadow as the night in the midst of the noonday. Hide the outcast. Be ray, not him that wandereth.

01:04:47.521 --> 01:05:07.441
Let mine outcast dwell with thee, Moab. Be thou a covert to them from the face of the spoiler. For the extortioner is at an end. The spoiler ceaseth. The oppressors are consumed out of the land.

01:05:07.441 --> 01:05:36.581
And in mercy shall the throne be established, and he shall sit upon it in truth, in the tabernacle of David judging, and seeking judgment, and hasting righteousness. We have heard of the pride of Moab. He is very proud even of his haughtiness, and his pride and his wrath, but his lies shall not be so.

01:05:36.581 --> 01:05:50.861
Therefore shall Moab howl for Moab. Everyone shall howl for the foundations of Kir-her-es-eth. Shall ye mourn? Surely they are stricken.

01:05:50.861 --> 01:06:12.081
For the fields of Heshbon languish, and the vine of Sibmah. The lords of the heathen have broken down the principal plants thereof. They are come even to Jazer. They wandered through the wilderness. Her branches are stretched out. They are gone over the sea.

01:06:12.081 --> 01:06:31.181
Therefore I will bewail with the weeping of Jazer, the vine of Sibmah. I will water thee with my tears, O Heshbon and Iliela, for the shouting of thy summer fruits, and for thy harvest is fallen.

01:06:31.181 --> 01:06:50.521
And gladness is taken away, and joy out of the plentiful field, and in the vineyards there shall be no singing, neither shall there be shouting. The treaders shall tread out no wine in their presses. I have made their vintage shouting to cease.

01:06:50.521 --> 01:07:13.701
Wherefore my bowels shall sound like an arp for Moab, and mine inward parts for Kir-her-esh. And it shall come to pass when it is seen that Moab is weary, on the high place that he shall come to his sanctuary to pray, but he shall not prevail.

01:07:13.701 --> 01:07:40.701
This is the word that the Lord hath spoken concerning Moab since that time. But now the Lord hath spoken, saying, Within three years, as the years of inhiling and the glory of Moab shall be condemned, with all that great multitude and the remnant shall be very small and feeble.

01:07:43.241 --> 01:08:02.641
The burden of Damascus. Behold, Damascus is taken away from being a city, and it shall be a ruinous heap. The cities of Aurora are forsaken. They shall be for flocks which shall lie down, and none shall make them afraid.

01:08:02.641 --> 01:08:17.121
The fortress also shall cease from Ephraim, and the kingdom from Damascus, and the remnant of Syria, they shall be as the glory of the children of Israel, saith the Lord of hosts.

01:08:17.121 --> 01:08:43.121
And in that day it shall come to pass, that the glory of Jacob shall be made thin, and the fatness of his flesh shall wax lean. And it shall be as when the harvest man gathereth the corn, and reapeth the ears with his arm, and it shall be as he that gathereth ears in the valley of Rephaim.

01:08:43.121 --> 01:09:05.581
Yet gleaning grapes shall be left in it, as the shaking of an olive tree, two or three berries in the top of the uppermost bough, four or five in the outmost fruitful branches thereof, saith the Lord God of Israel.

01:09:05.581 --> 01:09:26.941
At that day shall a man look to his Maker, and his eyes shall have respect to the Holy One of Israel. And he shall not look to the altars, the work of his hands, neither shall respect that which his fingers have made, either the grooves or the images.

01:09:26.941 --> 01:09:41.101
In that day shall his strong cities be as a forsaken bough, and an uppermost branch which they left because of the children of Israel, and there shall be desolation.

01:09:41.101 --> 01:09:57.421
Because thou hast forgotten the Lord of thy salvation, and hast not been mindful of the rock of thy strength, therefore shalt thou plant pleasant plants, and shalt set it with strange slips.

01:09:57.421 --> 01:10:13.341
In the day shalt thou make thy plant to grow, and in the morning shalt thou make thy seed to flourish. But the harvest shall be a heap in the day of grief and of desperate sorrow.

01:10:13.341 --> 01:10:27.401
Woe to the multitude of many people which make a noise like the noise of the seas, and to the rushing of nations that make a rushing like the rushing of mighty waters.

01:10:27.401 --> 01:10:46.581
The nations shall rush like the rushing of many waters, but God shall rebuke them, and they shall flee far off, and shall be chased as the shape of the mountains before the wind, and like a rolling thing before the whirlwind.

01:10:46.581 --> 01:10:59.581
And behold, at even tide trouble, and before the morning he is not. This is the portion of them that spoil us, and the lot of them that rob us.

01:11:02.561 --> 01:11:18.181
Woe to the land shadowing with wings, which is beyond the rivers of Ethiopia, that sendeth ambassadors by the sea, even in vessels of bull rushes upon the waters, saying,

01:11:18.181 --> 01:11:33.281
Go ye swift messengers, to a nation scattered and peeled, to a people terrible from their beginning hitherto, a nation meted out and trodden down, whose land the rivers have spoiled.

01:11:33.281 --> 01:11:46.801
All ye inhabitants of the world and dwellers on the earth, see ye when he lifteth up an ensign on the mountains, and when he bloweth the trumpet, hear ye.

01:11:46.801 --> 01:12:04.601
For so the Lord said unto me, I will take my rest, and I will consider in my dwelling place a clear heat upon herbs, and like a cloud of dew in the heat of harvest.

01:12:04.601 --> 01:12:20.481
For afore the harvest, when the bud is perfect, and the sour grape is ripening in the flower, he shall both cut off the sprigs with pruning hooks, and take away and cut down the branches.

01:12:20.481 --> 01:12:34.901
They shall be left together unto the fowls of the mountains, and to the beasts of the earth, and the fowls shall summer upon them, and all the beasts of the earth shall winter upon them.

01:12:34.901 --> 01:12:55.181
In that time shall the present be brought unto the Lord of hosts, of a people scattered and peeled, and from a people terrible from their beginning hitherto, a nation meted out and trodden underfoot, whose land the rivers have spoiled.

01:12:55.181 --> 01:13:10.701
To the place of the name of the Lord of hosts, the Mount of Zion.

01:13:38.652 --> 01:13:40.012
THE BURDEN OF EGYPT

01:13:40.012 --> 01:13:46.452
Behold, the LORD writeth upon a swift cloud, and shall come into Egypt, and the idols

01:13:46.452 --> 01:13:51.732
of Egypt shall be moved at his presence, and the heart of Egypt shall melt in the midst

01:13:51.732 --> 01:13:52.252
of it.

01:13:52.912 --> 01:13:58.252
And I will set the Egyptians against the Egyptians, and they shall fight every one against his

01:13:58.252 --> 01:14:03.752
brother, and every one against his neighbor, city against city, and kingdom against kingdom.

01:14:04.412 --> 01:14:09.492
And the spirit of Egypt shall fail in the midst thereof, and I will destroy the council

01:14:09.492 --> 01:14:13.952
thereof, and they shall seek to the idols, and to the charmers, and to them that have

01:14:13.952 --> 01:14:15.932
familiar spirits, and to the wizards.

01:14:16.752 --> 01:14:22.352
And the Egyptians will I give over into the hand of a cruel LORD, and a fierce king shall

01:14:22.352 --> 01:14:25.352
rule over them, said the LORD, the LORD of hosts.

01:14:26.252 --> 01:14:31.252
And the waters shall fail from the sea, and the river shall be wasted and dried up.

01:14:32.172 --> 01:14:37.672
And they shall turn the rivers far away, and the brooks of defense shall be emptied and

01:14:37.672 --> 01:14:38.292
dried up.

01:14:38.612 --> 01:14:40.692
The reeds and flags shall wither.

01:14:41.352 --> 01:14:46.212
The paper reeds by the brooks, by the mouth of the brooks, and everything sewn by the

01:14:46.212 --> 01:14:49.512
brooks, shall wither, be driven away, and be no more.

01:14:50.452 --> 01:14:56.392
The fishers also shall mourn, and all they that cast ankle into the brooks shall lament,

01:14:56.872 --> 01:14:59.892
and they that spread nets upon the waters shall languish.

01:15:00.552 --> 01:15:06.652
Moreover, they that work in fine flax, and they that weave networks, shall be confounded,

01:15:06.932 --> 01:15:12.912
and they shall be broken in the purposes thereof, all that make sluices and ponds for fish.

01:15:14.352 --> 01:15:16.792
Surely the princes of Zoan are fools.

01:15:17.172 --> 01:15:21.052
The counsel of the wise counselors of Pharaoh is become brutish.

01:15:21.312 --> 01:15:26.532
How say ye unto Pharaoh, I am the son of the wise, the son of ancient kings.

01:15:27.752 --> 01:15:28.772
Where are they?

01:15:29.172 --> 01:15:30.572
Where are thy wise men?

01:15:30.932 --> 01:15:36.832
And let them tell thee now, and let them know what the Lord of hosts hath purposed upon

01:15:36.832 --> 01:15:37.332
Egypt.

01:15:38.232 --> 01:15:40.612
The princes of Zoan are become fools.

01:15:41.112 --> 01:15:43.232
The princes of Noph are deceived.

01:15:43.652 --> 01:15:49.872
They have also seduced Egypt, even they that are the stay of the tribes thereof.

01:15:51.372 --> 01:15:56.332
The Lord hath mingled a perverse spirit in the midst thereof, and they have caused Egypt

01:15:56.332 --> 01:16:00.872
to err in every work thereof, as a drunken man staggereth in his vomit.

01:16:02.212 --> 01:16:07.512
Neither shall there be any work for Egypt, which the head or tail, branch or rush may

01:16:07.512 --> 01:16:07.952
do.

01:16:08.472 --> 01:16:13.692
In that day shall Egypt be like unto women, and it shall be afraid and feared because

01:16:13.692 --> 01:16:17.912
of the shaking of the hand of the Lord of hosts, which he shaketh over it.

01:16:18.612 --> 01:16:24.252
And the land of Judah shall be a terror unto Egypt, every one that maketh mention thereof

01:16:24.252 --> 01:16:29.132
shall be afraid in himself because of the counsel of the Lord of hosts, which he hath

01:16:29.132 --> 01:16:30.332
determined against it.

01:16:31.472 --> 01:16:37.112
In that day shall five cities in the land of Egypt speak the language of Canaan, and

01:16:37.112 --> 01:16:41.192
swear to the Lord of hosts, one shall be called the city of destruction.

01:16:42.012 --> 01:16:47.312
In that day shall there be an altar to the Lord in the midst of the land of Egypt, and

01:16:47.312 --> 01:16:49.452
a pillar at the border thereof to the Lord.

01:16:49.452 --> 01:16:54.892
And it shall be for a sign and for a witness unto the Lord of hosts in the land of Egypt,

01:16:55.372 --> 01:17:00.592
for they shall cry unto the Lord because of the oppressors, and he shall send them a Savior

01:17:00.592 --> 01:17:03.732
and a great one, and he shall deliver them.

01:17:04.352 --> 01:17:08.892
And the Lord shall be known to Egypt, and the Egyptians shall know the Lord in that

01:17:08.892 --> 01:17:14.292
day, and shall do sacrifice and oblation, yea, they shall vow a vow unto the Lord and

01:17:14.292 --> 01:17:15.112
perform it.

01:17:15.882 --> 01:17:21.592
And the Lord shall smite Egypt, he shall smite and heal it, and they shall return even to

01:17:21.592 --> 01:17:25.252
the Lord, and he shall be entreated of them, and shall heal them.

01:17:26.092 --> 01:17:31.832
In that day shall there be a highway out of Egypt to Syria, and the Assyrians shall come

01:17:31.832 --> 01:17:37.512
into Egypt and the Egyptians into Assyria, and the Egyptians shall serve with the Assyrians.

01:17:38.452 --> 01:17:43.802
In that day shall Israel be the third with Egypt and with Assyria, even a blessing in

01:17:43.802 --> 01:17:49.582
the midst of the land, whom the Lord of hosts shall bless, saying, Blessed be Egypt, my

01:17:49.582 --> 01:17:53.902
people, and Assyria, the work of my hands, and Israel, mine inheritance.

01:17:57.902 --> 01:18:03.902
In the year that Tartan came unto Ashdod, when Sargon the king of Assyria sent him,

01:18:04.242 --> 01:18:12.742
and fought against Ashdod and took it, at the same time spake the Lord by Isaiah the

01:18:12.742 --> 01:18:18.202
black cloth from off thy loins, and put off thy shoe from thy foot, and he did so, walking

01:18:18.202 --> 01:18:19.382
naked and barefoot.

01:18:20.002 --> 01:18:26.162
And the Lord said, Like as my servant Isaiah hath walked naked and barefoot three years,

01:18:26.562 --> 01:18:32.782
for a sign and wonder upon Egypt and upon Ethiopia, so shall the king of Assyria lead

01:18:32.782 --> 01:18:38.962
away the Egyptian prisoners and the Ethiopians captives, young and old, naked and barefoot,

01:18:38.962 --> 01:18:42.182
even with their buttocks uncovered, to the shame of Egypt.

01:18:43.262 --> 01:18:48.902
They shall be afraid, and ashamed of Ethiopia their expectation, and of Egypt their glory.

01:18:49.722 --> 01:18:55.602
And the inhabitant of this isle shall say in that day, Behold, such is our expectation,

01:18:56.202 --> 01:19:01.442
whither we flee for help to be delivered from the king of Assyria, and how shall we escape?

01:19:05.182 --> 01:19:07.262
The Burden of the Desert of the Sea

01:19:07.662 --> 01:19:12.122
As whirlwinds in the south pass through, so it cometh from the desert from a terrible

01:19:12.122 --> 01:19:12.502
land.

01:19:13.162 --> 01:19:18.342
A grievous vision is declared unto me, the treacherous dealer dealeth treacherously,

01:19:18.642 --> 01:19:20.082
and the spoiler spoileth.

01:19:20.662 --> 01:19:26.102
Go up, O Elam, besiege, O Media, all the sign thereof have I made to cease.

01:19:26.922 --> 01:19:32.542
Therefore are my loins filled with pain, pangs have taken hold upon me, as the pangs of a

01:19:32.542 --> 01:19:33.582
woman that travelleth.

01:19:33.942 --> 01:19:38.382
I was bowed down at the hearing of it, I was dismayed at the seeing of it.

01:19:39.062 --> 01:19:43.962
My heart panted, fearfulness affrightened me, the night of my pleasure hath he turned

01:19:43.962 --> 01:19:45.402
to do fear unto me.

01:19:45.802 --> 01:19:52.842
Prepare the table, watch in the watch-tower, eat, drink, arise ye princes, and anoint the

01:19:52.842 --> 01:19:53.202
shield.

01:19:54.382 --> 01:20:00.742
For thus hath the Lord said unto me, Go, set a watchman, let him declare what he seeth.

01:20:01.362 --> 01:20:07.862
And he saw a chariot with a couple of horsemen, a chariot of asses, and a chariot of camels,

01:20:08.082 --> 01:20:10.442
and he hearkened diligently with much heed.

01:20:11.002 --> 01:20:17.502
And he cried, A lion, my lord, I stand continually upon the watch-tower in the day-time, and

01:20:17.502 --> 01:20:20.402
I am set in my ward whole nights.

01:20:21.422 --> 01:20:25.782
And behold, here cometh a chariot of men with a couple of horsemen.

01:20:25.782 --> 01:20:31.502
And he answered and said, Babylon is fallen, is fallen, and all the graven images of her

01:20:31.502 --> 01:20:33.722
gods he hath broken unto the ground.

01:20:34.942 --> 01:20:40.682
O my threshing and the corn of my floor, that which I have heard of the Lord of hosts, the

01:20:40.682 --> 01:20:42.922
God of Israel, have I declared unto you.

01:20:44.422 --> 01:20:45.542
The burden of Duma.

01:20:46.302 --> 01:20:52.262
He calleth to me out of seer, Watchman, what of the night, watchman, what of the night?

01:20:52.802 --> 01:20:56.462
The watchman said, The morning cometh, and also the night.

01:20:56.902 --> 01:21:00.362
If ye will inquire, inquire ye, return, come.

01:21:01.602 --> 01:21:02.802
The burden upon Arabia.

01:21:03.282 --> 01:21:08.222
In the forest in Arabia shall ye lodge, O ye travelling companies of Dedanim.

01:21:08.922 --> 01:21:12.802
The inhabitants of the land of Tima brought water to him that was thirsty.

01:21:13.242 --> 01:21:15.602
They prevented with their bread him that fled.

01:21:16.462 --> 01:21:21.322
For they fled from the swords, from the drawn swords, and from the bent bow, and from the

01:21:21.322 --> 01:21:22.742
grievousness of war.

01:21:23.322 --> 01:21:29.102
For thus hath the Lord said unto me, Within a year, according to the years of an hireling,

01:21:29.462 --> 01:21:31.642
and all the glory of Keter shall fail.

01:21:32.122 --> 01:21:37.622
And the residue of the number of archers, the mighty men of the children of Keter, shall

01:21:37.622 --> 01:21:41.442
be diminished, for the Lord God of Israel hath spoken it.

01:21:59.458 --> 01:22:20.238
22. The Burden of the Valley of Vision. What aileth thee now, that thou art wholly gone

01:22:20.238 --> 01:22:26.838
up to the housetops? Thou that art full of stirs, a tumultuous city, joyous city, thy

01:22:26.838 --> 01:22:33.458
slain men are not slain with a sword, nor dead in battle. All thy rulers are fled together,

01:22:33.598 --> 01:22:39.038
they are bound by the archers. All that are found in thee are bound together, which have

01:22:39.038 --> 01:22:45.918
fled from afar. Therefore said I, Look away from me, I will weep bitterly. Labor not to

01:22:45.918 --> 01:22:50.118
comfort me, because of the spoiling of the daughter of my people. For it is a day of

01:22:50.118 --> 01:22:54.678
trouble, and of treading down, and of perplexity by the Lord God of Hosts in the Valley of

01:22:54.678 --> 01:23:00.338
Vision, breaking down the walls, and of crying to the mountains. And Elam bare the quiver

01:23:00.338 --> 01:23:06.238
with chariots of men and horsemen, and Curran covered the shield. And it shall come to pass,

01:23:06.518 --> 01:23:11.538
that thy choicest valleys shall be full of chariots, and the horsemen shall set themselves

01:23:11.538 --> 01:23:16.838
in array at the gate. And he discovered the covering of Judah, and now did its look in

01:23:16.838 --> 01:23:22.958
that day to the armor of the house of the forest. Ye have seen also the breaches of

01:23:22.958 --> 01:23:28.398
the city of David, that they are many, and ye gathered together the waters of the lower

01:23:28.398 --> 01:23:34.958
pool. And ye have numbered the houses of Jerusalem, and the houses have ye broken down to fortify

01:23:34.958 --> 01:23:40.958
the wall. Ye made also a ditch between the two walls for the water of the old pool, but

01:23:40.958 --> 01:23:45.658
ye have not looked unto the Maker thereof, neither had respect unto him that fashioned

01:23:45.658 --> 01:23:51.898
it long ago. And in that day did the Lord God of Hosts call to weeping, and to mourning,

01:23:52.298 --> 01:23:58.678
and to baldness, and to girding with sackcloth, and behold joy and gladness, slaying oxen,

01:23:58.758 --> 01:24:04.378
and killing sheep, eating flesh, and drinking wine. Let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we

01:24:04.378 --> 01:24:10.278
shall die. And it was revealed in mine ears by the Lord of Hosts, surely this iniquity

01:24:10.278 --> 01:24:15.638
shall not be purged from you till ye die, said the Lord God of Hosts. Thus said the

01:24:15.638 --> 01:24:21.358
Lord God of Hosts, Go, get thee unto this treasurer, even unto Shebna, which is over

01:24:21.358 --> 01:24:28.018
the house, and say, What hast thou here, and whom hast thou here, that thou hast hewed

01:24:28.018 --> 01:24:34.358
thee out a sepulchre here, as he that heweth him out a sepulchre on high, and that graveth

01:24:34.358 --> 01:24:40.258
an habitation for himself in a rock? Behold, the Lord will carry thee away with a mighty

01:24:40.258 --> 01:24:46.098
captivity, and will surely cover thee. He will surely violently turn and toss thee like

01:24:46.098 --> 01:24:53.378
a ball into a large country. There shalt thou die, and there the chariots of thy glory

01:24:53.378 --> 01:24:59.558
shall be the shame of thy Lord's house. And I will drive thee from thy station, and from

01:24:59.558 --> 01:25:05.398
thy state shall he pull thee down. And it shall come to pass in that day, that I will

01:25:05.398 --> 01:25:11.618
call my servant Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, and I will clothe him with thy robe, and strengthen

01:25:11.618 --> 01:25:17.218
him with thy girdle. And I will commit thy government into his hand, and he shall be

01:25:17.218 --> 01:25:23.218
a father to the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and to the house of Judah. And the key of

01:25:23.218 --> 01:25:31.958
the house of David will I lay upon his shoulder, so he shall open, and none shall shut, and

01:25:31.958 --> 01:25:37.538
I will fasten him as a nail in a sure place, and he shall be for a glorious throne to his

01:25:37.538 --> 01:25:43.858
father's house. And they shall hang upon him all the glory of his father's house, the offspring

01:25:43.858 --> 01:25:49.278
and the issue, all vessels of small quantity, from the vessels of cups even to the vessels

01:25:49.278 --> 01:25:55.458
of flagons. In that day, saith the Lord of hosts, shall the nail that is fastened in

01:25:55.458 --> 01:26:01.198
the sure place be removed, and be cut down, and fall, and the burden that was upon it

01:26:01.198 --> 01:26:04.178
shall be cut off, for the Lord hath spoken it.

01:26:07.678 --> 01:26:09.398
The Burden of Tyre

01:26:09.398 --> 01:26:15.998
How ye ships of Tarshish! for it is laid waste, so that there is no house, no entering in,

01:26:16.238 --> 01:26:22.738
from the land of Ketim it is revealed to them. Be still ye inhabitants of the Isle, thou

01:26:22.738 --> 01:26:27.798
whom the merchants of Zidon that pass over the sea have replenished, and by great waters

01:26:27.798 --> 01:26:33.178
the seed of Sihor, the harvest of the river, is her revenue, and she is a mart of nations.

01:26:34.018 --> 01:26:39.278
Be thou ashamed, O Zidon, for the sea hath spoken even the strength of the sea, saying,

01:26:39.438 --> 01:26:46.498
I travel not, nor bring forth children, neither do I nourish up young men, nor bring up virgins.

01:26:47.638 --> 01:26:53.658
As at the report concerning Egypt, so shall they be sorely pained at the report of Tyre.

01:26:54.018 --> 01:27:00.918
Pass ye over to Tarshish! How, ye inhabitants of the Isle! Is this your joyous city, whose

01:27:00.918 --> 01:27:07.978
antiquity is of ancient days? Her own feet shall carry her far off to Sojourn. Who hath

01:27:07.978 --> 01:27:14.238
taken this council against Tyre, the crowning city, whose merchants are princes, whose traffickers

01:27:14.238 --> 01:27:20.158
are the honourable of the earth? The Lord of Hosts hath purposed it, to stain the pride

01:27:20.158 --> 01:27:24.238
of all glory, and to bring into contempt all the honourable of the earth.

01:27:25.458 --> 01:27:31.378
Pass through thy land as a river, O daughter of Tarshish, there is no more strength. He

01:27:31.378 --> 01:27:37.718
stretched out his hand over the sea, he shook the kingdoms, the Lord hath given a commandment

01:27:37.718 --> 01:27:43.378
against the merchant city, to destroy the strongholds thereof. And he said, Thou shalt

01:27:43.378 --> 01:27:49.798
no more rejoice, O thou oppressed virgin, daughter of Zidon, arise, pass over to Khitim,

01:27:50.218 --> 01:27:56.298
there also shalt thou have no rest. Behold, the land of the Chaldeans, this people was

01:27:56.298 --> 01:28:01.158
not till the Assyrians founded it for them that dwell in the wilderness. They set up

01:28:01.158 --> 01:28:05.578
the towers thereof, they raised up the palaces thereof, and he brought it to ruin.

01:28:06.598 --> 01:28:11.758
How ye ships of Tarshish, for your strength is laid waste, and it shall come to pass in

01:28:11.758 --> 01:28:17.198
that day, that Tyre shall be forgotten seventy years, according to the days of one king,

01:28:17.358 --> 01:28:23.498
after the end of seventy years, shall Tyre sing as in harlot. Take and harp, go about

01:28:23.498 --> 01:28:30.518
the city, thou harlot that hast been forgotten, make sweet melody, sing many songs, that thou

01:28:30.518 --> 01:28:36.138
mayest be remembered. And it shall come to pass, after the end of seventy years, that

01:28:36.138 --> 01:28:40.978
the Lord will visit Tyre, and she shall turn to her hire, and shall commit fornication

01:28:40.978 --> 01:28:46.538
with all the kingdoms of the world upon the face of the earth. And her merchandise and

01:28:46.538 --> 01:28:51.978
her hire shall be holiness to the Lord, it shall not be treasured nor laid up, for her

01:28:51.978 --> 01:28:57.058
merchandise shall be for them that dwell before the Lord, to eat sufficiently, and for durable

01:28:57.058 --> 01:28:57.578
clothing.

01:28:59.898 --> 01:29:04.278
Behold, the Lord maketh the earth empty,

01:29:04.438 --> 01:29:09.498
and maketh it waste, and turneth it upside down, and scattereth abroad the inhabitants

01:29:09.498 --> 01:29:15.718
thereof. And it shall be, as with the people, so with the priest, as with the servant, so

01:29:15.718 --> 01:29:21.478
with his master, as with the maid, so with her mistress, as with the buyer, so with the

01:29:21.478 --> 01:29:27.158
seller, as with the lender, so with the borrower, as with the taker of usury, so with the giver

01:29:27.158 --> 01:29:32.898
of usury to him. The land shall be utterly emptied and utterly spoiled, for the Lord

01:29:32.898 --> 01:29:39.038
hath spoken this word. The earth mourneth and fadeth away, the world languisheth and

01:29:39.038 --> 01:29:45.098
fadeth away, the haughty people of the earth do languish. The earth also is defiled under

01:29:45.098 --> 01:29:50.098
the inhabitants thereof, because they have transgressed the laws, changed the ordinance,

01:29:50.518 --> 01:29:56.018
broken the everlasting covenant. Therefore hath the curse devoured the earth, and they

01:29:56.018 --> 01:30:00.738
that dwell therein are desolate, therefore the inhabitants of the earth are burned and

01:30:00.738 --> 01:30:08.398
few men left. The new wine mourneth, the vine languisheth, all the merry-hearted do sigh.

01:30:09.098 --> 01:30:14.898
The mirth of tabarettes ceaseth, the noise of them that rejoice endeth, the joy of the

01:30:14.898 --> 01:30:21.338
harp ceaseth. They shall not drink wine with a song, strong drink shall be bitter to them

01:30:21.338 --> 01:30:27.558
that drink it. The city of confusion is broken down, every house is shut up, that no man

01:30:27.558 --> 01:30:33.258
may come in. There is a crying for wine in the streets, all joy is darkened, the mirth

01:30:33.258 --> 01:30:39.878
of the land is gone. In the city is left desolation, and the gate is smitten with destruction.

01:30:40.718 --> 01:30:45.138
When thus it shall be in the midst of the land among the people, there shall be as the

01:30:45.138 --> 01:30:50.318
shaking of an olive tree, and as the gleaning grapes when the vintage is gone. They shall

01:30:50.318 --> 01:30:54.838
lift up their voices, they shall sing for the majesty of the Lord, they shall cry aloud

01:30:54.838 --> 01:31:00.478
from the sea. Wherefore glorify ye the Lord in the fires, even the name of the Lord God

01:31:00.478 --> 01:31:06.478
of Israel in the isle of the sea. From the uttermost part of the earth have we heard

01:31:06.478 --> 01:31:13.178
songs, even glory to the righteous, but I said, My leanness, my leanness woe unto me,

01:31:13.398 --> 01:31:18.638
the treacherous dealers have dealt treacherously, yea the treacherous dealers have dealt very

01:31:18.638 --> 01:31:24.598
treacherously. Fear and the pit and the snare are upon thee, O inhabitant of the earth,

01:31:25.138 --> 01:31:31.378
and it shall come to pass, that he who fleeeth from the noise of the fear shall fall into

01:31:31.378 --> 01:31:36.298
the pit, and he that cometh up out of the midst of the pit shall be taken in the snare,

01:31:36.758 --> 01:31:41.958
for the windows from on high are open, and the foundations of the earth do shake, and

01:31:41.958 --> 01:31:47.738
the earth is utterly broken down, the earth is clean dissolved, the earth is moved exceedingly.

01:31:48.338 --> 01:31:53.718
The earth shall reel to and fro like a trunkard, and shall be removed like a cottage, and

01:31:53.718 --> 01:31:58.578
the transgression thereof shall be heavy upon it, and it shall fall and not rise again,

01:31:59.058 --> 01:32:03.318
and it shall come to pass in that day, that the Lord shall punish the host of the high

01:32:03.318 --> 01:32:09.218
ones that are on high, and the kings of the earth upon the earth, and they shall be gathered

01:32:09.218 --> 01:32:14.098
together as prisoners are gathered in the pit, and shall be shut up in the prison, and

01:32:14.098 --> 01:32:19.678
after many days shall they be visited. Then the moon shall be confounded, and the sun

01:32:19.678 --> 01:32:25.798
ashamed, when the Lord of hosts shall reign in Mt. Zion, and in Jerusalem, and before his

01:32:25.798 --> 01:32:27.138
angels gloriously.

01:32:39.350 --> 01:33:01.130
25. O Lord, thou art my God! I will exalt thee, I will praise thy name, for thou hast done

01:33:01.130 --> 01:33:06.270
wonderful things, thy counsels of old are faithfulness and truth, for thou hast made

01:33:06.270 --> 01:33:12.530
of a city a heap, of a defenced city a ruin, a palace of strangers to be no city, it shall

01:33:12.530 --> 01:33:17.490
never be built. Therefore shall the strong people glorify thee, the city of the terrible

01:33:17.490 --> 01:33:22.310
nations shall fear thee, for thou hast been a strength to the poor, a strength to the

01:33:22.310 --> 01:33:27.470
needy in his distress, a refuge from the storm, a shadow from the heat, when the blast of

01:33:27.470 --> 01:33:32.770
the terrible ones is as a storm against the wall. Thou shalt bring down the noise of strangers,

01:33:32.770 --> 01:33:38.630
as the heat in a dry place, even the heat with the shadow of a cloud, the branch of the terrible

01:33:38.630 --> 01:33:44.350
ones shall be brought low. And in this mountain shall the Lord of hosts make unto all people a

01:33:44.350 --> 01:33:50.670
feast of fat things, a feast of wines on the lees, of fat things full of marrow, of wines on the lees

01:33:50.670 --> 01:33:56.110
well refined. And he will destroy in this mountain the face of the covering cast over all people,

01:33:56.430 --> 01:34:02.010
and the veil that is spread over all nations. He will swallow up death in victory, and the Lord God

01:34:02.010 --> 01:34:07.430
will wipe away tears from off all faces, and the rebuke of his people shall he take away from off

01:34:07.430 --> 01:34:13.550
all the earth, for the Lord hath spoken it. And it shall be said in that day, Lo, this is our God,

01:34:13.810 --> 01:34:18.830
we have waited for him, and he will save us, this is the Lord, we have waited for him, we will be

01:34:18.830 --> 01:34:24.350
glad and rejoice in his salvation. For in this mountain shall the hand of the Lord rest, and Moab

01:34:24.350 --> 01:34:29.770
shall be trodden down under him, even as straw is trodden down for the dung hill. And he shall

01:34:29.770 --> 01:34:34.670
spread forth his hands in the midst of them, as he that swimmeth spreadeth forth his hands to swim,

01:34:35.090 --> 01:34:39.890
and he shall bring down their pride together with the spoils of their hands. And the fortress of the

01:34:39.890 --> 01:34:45.370
high fort of thy walls shall he bring down, lay low, and bring to the ground, even to the dust.

01:34:46.230 --> 01:34:52.670
In that day shall this song be sung in the land of Judah. We have a strong city,

01:34:53.230 --> 01:34:58.010
salvation will God appoint for the walls and bulwarks. Open ye the gates that the righteous

01:34:58.010 --> 01:35:02.570
nation which keepeth the truth may enter in. Thou wilt keep him in perfect peace,

01:35:02.710 --> 01:35:07.410
whose mind is stayed on thee, because he trusteth in thee. Trust ye in the Lord forever,

01:35:07.750 --> 01:35:12.590
for in the Lord Jehovah is everlasting strength. For he bringeth down them that dwell on high.

01:35:12.850 --> 01:35:18.430
The lofty city he layeth it low, he layeth it low even to the ground, he bringeth it even to the dust.

01:35:18.830 --> 01:35:22.770
The foot shall tread it down, even the feet of the poor, and the steps of the needy.

01:35:22.770 --> 01:35:28.230
The way of the just is uprightness. Thou most upright dost weigh the path of the just.

01:35:29.110 --> 01:35:32.150
Yea, in the way of thy judgments, O Lord, we have waited for thee.

01:35:32.450 --> 01:35:36.510
The desire of our soul is to thy name, and to the remembrance of thee.

01:35:37.210 --> 01:35:42.130
With my soul have I desired thee in the night. Yea, with my spirit within me will I seek thee

01:35:42.130 --> 01:35:47.290
early. For when thy judgments are in the earth, the inhabitants of the world will learn righteousness.

01:35:48.010 --> 01:35:51.710
Let favor be showed to the wicked, yet will he not learn righteousness.

01:35:52.290 --> 01:35:57.150
In the land of uprightness will he deal unjustly, and will not behold the majesty of the Lord.

01:35:57.830 --> 01:36:01.570
Lord, when thy hand is lifted up, they will not see, but they shall see,

01:36:01.750 --> 01:36:06.510
and be ashamed for their envy at the people. Yea, the fire of thine enemies shall devour them.

01:36:06.970 --> 01:36:12.310
Lord, thou wilt ordain peace for us, for thou also hast wrought all our works in us.

01:36:12.310 --> 01:36:18.670
O Lord our God, other Lords beside thee have had dominion over us, but by thee only will we make

01:36:18.670 --> 01:36:24.170
mention of thy name. They are dead, they shall not live. They are deceased, they shall not rise.

01:36:24.630 --> 01:36:28.930
Therefore hast thou visited and destroyed them, and made all their memory to perish.

01:36:29.510 --> 01:36:33.190
Thou hast increased the nation, O Lord. Thou hast increased the nation.

01:36:33.610 --> 01:36:37.930
Thou art glorified. Thou hast removed it far unto all the ends of the earth.

01:36:38.490 --> 01:36:43.850
Lord, in trouble have they visited thee. They poured out a prayer when thy chastening was

01:36:43.850 --> 01:36:48.870
upon them. Like as a woman with child that draweth near the time of her delivery is in pain,

01:36:49.230 --> 01:36:54.990
and crieth out in her pangs, so have we been in thy sight, O Lord. We have been with child,

01:36:55.210 --> 01:37:00.630
we have been in pain, we have as it were brought forth wind, we have not wrought any deliverance

01:37:00.630 --> 01:37:05.670
in the earth, neither have the inhabitants of the world fallen. Thy dead men shall live,

01:37:05.670 --> 01:37:10.650
together with my dead body shall they arise. Awake and sing, ye that dwell in the dust,

01:37:10.910 --> 01:37:16.230
for thy dew is as the dew of herbs, and the earth shall cast out the dead. Come, my people,

01:37:16.610 --> 01:37:21.090
enter thou into thy chambers, and shut thy doors about thee. Hide thyself, as it were,

01:37:21.110 --> 01:37:26.370
for a little moment, until the indignation be overpassed. For behold, the Lord cometh out of

01:37:26.370 --> 01:37:31.470
his place to punish the inhabitants of the earth for their iniquity. The earth also shall disclose

01:37:31.470 --> 01:37:38.950
her blood, and shall no more cover her slain. In that day the Lord with his saw

01:37:38.950 --> 01:37:45.170
and great and strong sword shall punish Leviathan the piercing serpent, even Leviathan that crooked

01:37:45.170 --> 01:37:51.650
serpent, and he shall slay the dragon that is in the sea. In that day sing ye unto her a vineyard

01:37:51.650 --> 01:37:58.050
of red wine. I the Lord do keep it, I will water it every moment, lest any hurt it I will keep it

01:37:58.050 --> 01:38:03.470
night and day. Fury is not in me. Who would set the briers and thorns against me in battle?

01:38:03.710 --> 01:38:08.410
I would go through them, I would burn them together. Or let him take hold of my strength,

01:38:08.630 --> 01:38:13.950
that he may make peace with me, and he shall make peace with me. He shall cause them that come of

01:38:13.950 --> 01:38:18.990
Jacob to take root. Israel shall blossom and bud, and fill the face of the world with fruit.

01:38:19.690 --> 01:38:24.890
Hath he smitten him, as he smote those that smote him? Or is he slain according to the

01:38:24.890 --> 01:38:28.990
order of them that are slain by him? In measure, when it shooteth forth,

01:38:29.290 --> 01:38:35.490
thou wilt debate with it. He stayeth this rough wind in the day of the east wind. By this therefore

01:38:35.490 --> 01:38:41.030
shall the iniquity of Jacob be purged, and this is all the fruit to take away his sin. When he

01:38:41.030 --> 01:38:45.670
maketh all the stones of the altar as chalk stones that are beaten in the sunder, the groves and

01:38:45.670 --> 01:38:51.690
images shall not stand up. Yet the defenced city shall be desolate, and the habitation forsaken and

01:38:51.690 --> 01:38:56.870
left like a wilderness. There shall the calf feed, and there shall he lie down and consume the

01:38:56.870 --> 01:39:01.490
branches thereof. When the boughs thereof are withered, they shall be broken off. The women

01:39:01.490 --> 01:39:07.150
come and set them on fire, for it is a people of no understanding. Therefore he that made them will

01:39:07.150 --> 01:39:12.670
not have mercy on them, and he that formed them will show them no favour. And it shall come to

01:39:12.670 --> 01:39:17.030
pass in that day, that the Lord shall beat off from the channel of the river unto the stream of

01:39:17.030 --> 01:39:22.750
Egypt, and ye shall be gathered one by one, O ye children of Israel. And it shall come to pass

01:39:22.750 --> 01:39:27.430
in that day, that the great trumpet shall be blown, and they shall come which were ready to

01:39:27.430 --> 01:39:32.650
perish in the land of Assyria and the outcasts in the land of Egypt, and shall worship the Lord

01:39:32.650 --> 01:39:38.150
in the holy mount at Jerusalem.

01:39:53.841 --> 01:40:03.561
28. Woe to the crown of pride, to the drunkards of Ephraim, whose glorious beauty is a fading

01:40:03.561 --> 01:40:08.981
flower, which are on the head of the fat valleys of them that are overcome with wine. Behold,

01:40:08.981 --> 01:40:13.921
the Lord hath a mighty and strong one, which as a tempest of hail and a destroying storm,

01:40:14.261 --> 01:40:19.781
as a flood of mighty waters overflowing, shall cast down to the earth with the hand. The crown

01:40:19.781 --> 01:40:24.401
of pride, the drunkards of Ephraim, shall be trodden under feet, and the glorious beauty which is on

01:40:24.401 --> 01:40:29.261
the head of the fat valley shall be a fading flower, and as the hasty fruit before the summer,

01:40:29.581 --> 01:40:35.201
which when he that looketh upon it seeth, while it is yet in his hand, he eateth it up. In that

01:40:35.201 --> 01:40:40.281
day shall the Lord of hosts be for a crown of glory, and for a diadem of beauty unto the residue

01:40:40.281 --> 01:40:45.481
of his people, and for a spirit of judgment to him that sitteth in judgment, and for strength

01:40:45.481 --> 01:40:50.661
to them that turn the battle to the gate. But they also have erred through wine, and through

01:40:50.661 --> 01:40:54.901
strong drink are out of the way. The priest and the prophet have erred through strong drink,

01:40:55.101 --> 01:40:59.661
they are swallowed up of wine, they are out of the way through strong drink, they err in vision,

01:40:59.981 --> 01:41:04.921
they stumble in judgment. For all the tables are full of vomit and filthiness, so that there is

01:41:04.921 --> 01:41:10.101
no place clean. Whom shall he teach knowledge, and whom shall he make to understand doctrine?

01:41:10.661 --> 01:41:15.961
Them that are weaned from the milk and drawn from the breasts. For precept must be upon precept,

01:41:16.261 --> 01:41:22.541
precept upon precept, line upon line, line upon line, here a little and there a little. For with

01:41:22.541 --> 01:41:28.161
stammering lips and another tongue will he speak to this people. To whom he said, This is the rest

01:41:28.161 --> 01:41:33.941
wherewith ye may cause the weary to rest, and this is the refreshing. Yet they would not hear. But the

01:41:33.941 --> 01:41:39.221
word of the Lord was unto them, precept upon precept, precept upon precept, line upon line,

01:41:39.561 --> 01:41:45.301
line upon line, here a little and there a little, that they might go and fall backward, and be broken

01:41:45.301 --> 01:41:50.681
and snared and taken. Wherefore hear the word of the Lord, ye scornful men, that rule this people

01:41:50.681 --> 01:41:55.801
which is in Jerusalem. Because ye have said, We have made a covenant with death, and with hell

01:41:55.801 --> 01:42:00.761
we are at agreement. When the overflowing scourge shall pass through, it shall not come unto us.

01:42:00.761 --> 01:42:06.481
For we have made lies our refuge, and under falsehood we have hid ourselves. Therefore thus saith the

01:42:06.481 --> 01:42:12.841
Lord God, Behold, I lay in Zion for a foundation, a stone, a tried stone, a precious cornerstone,

01:42:13.161 --> 01:42:18.801
a sure foundation. He that believeth shall not make haste. Judgment also will I lay to the line,

01:42:19.201 --> 01:42:23.941
and righteousness to the plummet. And the hail shall sweep away the refuge of lies, and the

01:42:23.941 --> 01:42:28.961
waters shall overflow the hiding place. And your covenant with death shall be disannulled,

01:42:28.961 --> 01:42:33.881
and your agreement with hell shall not stand. When the overflowing scourge shall pass through,

01:42:34.181 --> 01:42:38.981
then ye shall be trodden down by it. From the time that it goeth forth, it shall take you. For

01:42:38.981 --> 01:42:43.941
morning by morning shall it pass over, by day and by night. And it shall be a vexation only to

01:42:43.941 --> 01:42:48.561
understand the report. For the bed is shorter than that a man can stretch himself on it,

01:42:48.641 --> 01:42:53.141
and the covering narrower than that he can wrap himself in it. For the Lord shall rise up,

01:42:53.321 --> 01:42:58.181
as in Mount Perazim. He shall be wroth as in the valley of Gibeon, that he may do his work,

01:42:58.181 --> 01:43:04.161
his strange work, and bring to pass his act, his strange act. Now therefore be ye not mockers,

01:43:04.281 --> 01:43:08.461
lest your bands be made strong. For I have heard from the Lord God of hosts a consumption,

01:43:08.821 --> 01:43:13.661
even determined upon the whole earth. Give ye ear, and hear my voice. Harken, and hear my speech.

01:43:13.921 --> 01:43:19.441
Doth the ploughman plough all day to sow? Doth he open and break the clods of his ground? When he

01:43:19.441 --> 01:43:24.121
hath made plain the face thereof, doth he not cast abroad the fitches, and scatter the cumin,

01:43:24.121 --> 01:43:28.461
and cast in the principal wheat, and in the appointed barley, and the rye in their place?

01:43:28.641 --> 01:43:33.161
For his God doth instruct him to discretion, and doth teach him. For the fitches are not threshed

01:43:33.161 --> 01:43:37.601
with a threshing instrument, neither is the cart wheel turned about upon the common. But the

01:43:37.601 --> 01:43:42.121
fitches are beaten out with a staff, and the common with a rod. Breadcorn is bruised, because

01:43:42.121 --> 01:43:46.201
he will not ever be threshing it, nor break it with the wheel of his cart, nor bruise it with

01:43:46.201 --> 01:43:50.761
his horsemen. This also cometh forth from the Lord of hosts, which is wonderful in counsel,

01:43:50.761 --> 01:43:54.881
and excellent in working. Isaiah chapter 29.

01:43:55.521 --> 01:44:02.001
Woe to Ariel, to Ariel the city where David dwelt! Add ye year to year, let them kill sacrifices.

01:44:02.501 --> 01:44:07.361
Yet I will distress Ariel, and there shall be heaviness and sorrow, and it shall be unto me as

01:44:07.361 --> 01:44:12.321
Ariel. And I will camp against thee round about, and will lay siege against thee with a mount,

01:44:12.421 --> 01:44:16.561
and I will raise forts against thee. And thou shalt be brought down, and thou shalt speak out

01:44:16.561 --> 01:44:21.621
the ground, and thy speech shall be low out of the dust, and thy voice shall be as of one that

01:44:21.621 --> 01:44:26.021
hath a familiar spirit out of the ground, and thy speech shall whisper out of the dust.

01:44:26.661 --> 01:44:31.061
Moreover, the multitude of thy strangers shall be like small dust, and the multitude of the

01:44:31.061 --> 01:44:36.381
terrible ones shall be as chuff that passeth away. Yea, it shall be at an instant suddenly.

01:44:36.721 --> 01:44:41.201
Thou shalt be visited of the Lord of hosts with thunder, and with earthquake, and great noise,

01:44:41.201 --> 01:44:46.941
with storm and tempest, and the flame of devouring fire. And the multitude of all the nations that

01:44:46.941 --> 01:44:51.761
fight against Ariel, even all that fight against her and her munition, and that distress her,

01:44:51.981 --> 01:44:57.221
shall be as a dream of a night vision. It shall even be as when a hungry man dreameth, and behold

01:44:57.221 --> 01:45:02.801
he eateth, but he awakeeth, and his soul is empty. Or as when a thirsty man dreameth, and behold he

01:45:02.801 --> 01:45:08.541
drinketh, but he awakeeth, and behold he is faint, and his soul hath appetite. So shall the multitude

01:45:08.541 --> 01:45:14.181
of all the nations be that fight against Mount Zion. Stay yourselves and wonder. Cry ye out,

01:45:14.301 --> 01:45:19.441
and cry, They are drunken, but not with wine. They stagger, but not with strong drink. For the Lord

01:45:19.441 --> 01:45:24.721
hath poured out upon you the spirit of deep sleep, and hath closed your eyes. The prophets and your

01:45:24.721 --> 01:45:29.741
rulers, the seers, hath he covered. And the vision of all is become unto you as the words of a book

01:45:29.741 --> 01:45:34.821
that is sealed, which men deliver to one that is learned, saying, Read this, I pray thee. And he

01:45:34.821 --> 01:45:39.381
saith, I cannot, for it is sealed. And the book is delivered to him that is not learned, saying,

01:45:39.421 --> 01:45:44.141
Read this, I pray thee. And he saith, I am not learned. For as much as this people draw near me

01:45:44.141 --> 01:45:48.381
with their mouth, and with their lips do honour me, but have removed their heart far from me,

01:45:48.621 --> 01:45:54.121
and their fear toward me is taught by the precept of men. Therefore, behold, I will proceed to do a

01:45:54.121 --> 01:45:59.501
marvellous work among this people, even a marvellous work and a wonder. For the wisdom of their wise

01:45:59.501 --> 01:46:04.421
men shall perish, and the understanding of their prudent men shall be hid. Woe unto them that seek

01:46:04.421 --> 01:46:08.961
deep to hide their counsel from the Lord, and their works are in the dark, and they say, Who

01:46:08.961 --> 01:46:14.261
seeth us, and who knoweth us? Surely your turning of things upside down shall be esteemed as the

01:46:14.261 --> 01:46:20.001
potter's clay. For shall the work say of him that made it, He made me not? Or shall the thing framed

01:46:20.001 --> 01:46:25.801
say of him that framed it, He had no understanding. Is it not yet a very little while, and Lebanon shall

01:46:25.801 --> 01:46:34.181
be turned into a fruitful field, and the fruitful field shall be esteemed as a forest? And in that

01:46:34.181 --> 01:46:39.661
shall see out of obscurity and out of darkness. The meek also shall increase their joy in the Lord,

01:46:40.021 --> 01:46:44.681
and the poor among men shall rejoice in the Holy One of Israel. For the terrible one is brought

01:46:44.681 --> 01:46:50.361
to nought, and the scorner is consumed, and all that watch for iniquity are cut off. That make a

01:46:50.361 --> 01:46:54.861
man an offender for a word, and lay a snare for him that reproveeth in the gate, and turn aside

01:46:54.861 --> 01:46:59.741
the just for a thing of nought. Therefore thus saith the Lord who redeemed Abraham concerning the

01:46:59.741 --> 01:47:06.061
Jacob. Jacob shall not now be ashamed, neither shall his face now wax pale. But when he seeth

01:47:06.061 --> 01:47:11.421
his children, the work of mine hands in the midst of him, they shall sanctify my name, and sanctify

01:47:11.421 --> 01:47:16.901
the Holy One of Jacob, and shall fear the God of Israel. They also that erred in spirit shall come

01:47:16.901 --> 01:47:23.241
to understanding, and they that murmured shall learn doctrine. Isaiah chapter 30. Woe to the

01:47:23.241 --> 01:47:27.881
rebellious children, saith the Lord, that take counsel but not of me, and that cover with the

01:47:27.881 --> 01:47:33.061
covering, but not of my spirit, that they may add sin to sin, that walk to go down into Egypt,

01:47:33.181 --> 01:47:37.821
and have not asked at my mouth, to strengthen themselves in the strength of Pharaoh, and to

01:47:37.821 --> 01:47:42.921
trust in the shadow of Egypt. Therefore shall the strength of Pharaoh be your shame, and the trust

01:47:42.921 --> 01:47:48.041
in the shadow of Egypt your confusion. For his princes were at Zohan, and his ambassadors came

01:47:48.041 --> 01:47:53.221
to Hainis. They were all ashamed for people that could not profit them, nor be in help nor profit,

01:47:53.221 --> 01:47:58.541
but a shame, and also a reproach. The burden of the beasts of the south, into the land of trouble

01:47:58.541 --> 01:48:03.881
and anguish, from whence came the young and old lion, the viper and fiery flying serpent. They will

01:48:03.881 --> 01:48:07.961
carry their riches upon the shoulders of young asses, and their treasures upon the bunches of

01:48:07.961 --> 01:48:12.501
camels, to a people that shall not profit them. For the Egyptians shall help in vain, and to no

01:48:12.501 --> 01:48:18.801
purpose. Therefore have I cried concerning this. Their strength is to sit still. Now go, write it

01:48:18.801 --> 01:48:23.501
for them in a table, and note it in a book, that it may be for the time to come forever and ever,

01:48:23.601 --> 01:48:28.261
that this is a rebellious people, lying children, children that will not hear the law of the Lord,

01:48:28.701 --> 01:48:33.681
which say to the seers, see not, and to the prophets, prophesy not unto us right things,

01:48:33.941 --> 01:48:39.661
speak unto us smooth things, prophesy deceits, get you out of the way, turn aside out of the path,

01:48:39.741 --> 01:48:44.881
cause the Holy One of Israel to cease from before us. Wherefore thus saith the Holy One of Israel,

01:48:44.881 --> 01:48:49.401
because you despise this word, and trust in oppression and perverseness, and stay thereon,

01:48:49.821 --> 01:48:54.701
therefore this iniquity shall be to you as a breach ready to fall, swelling out in a high wall,

01:48:55.001 --> 01:49:00.201
whose breaking cometh suddenly at an instant. And he shall break it as the breaking of the potter's

01:49:00.201 --> 01:49:05.021
vessel that is broken in pieces. He shall not spare, so that there shall not be found in the

01:49:05.021 --> 01:49:09.401
bursting of it a shard to take fire from the hearth, or to take water withal out of the pit.

01:49:10.021 --> 01:49:14.861
For thus saith the Lord God, the Holy One of Israel, in returning and rest shall you be saved.

01:49:14.881 --> 01:49:20.221
In quietness and in confidence shall be your strength, and ye would not. But ye said,

01:49:20.421 --> 01:49:25.921
No, for we will flee upon horses, therefore shall ye flee. And we will ride upon the swift,

01:49:26.401 --> 01:49:30.941
therefore shall they that pursue you be swift. One thousand shall flee at the rebuke of one,

01:49:31.281 --> 01:49:35.901
at the rebuke of five shall ye flee, till ye be left as a beacon upon the top of a mountain,

01:49:36.221 --> 01:49:41.561
and as an ensign on a hill. And therefore will the Lord wait, that he may be gracious unto you,

01:49:41.561 --> 01:49:46.901
and therefore will he be exalted, that he may have mercy upon you. For the Lord is a God of judgment,

01:49:47.321 --> 01:49:51.521
blessed are all they that wait for him. For the people shall dwell in Zion at Jerusalem,

01:49:52.001 --> 01:49:55.881
thou shalt weep no more, he will be very gracious unto thee at the voice of thy cry.

01:49:56.241 --> 01:50:00.541
When he shall hear it, he will answer thee. And though the Lord give you the bread of adversity

01:50:00.541 --> 01:50:05.261
and the water of affliction, yet shall not thy textures be removed into a corner any more,

01:50:05.461 --> 01:50:10.221
but thine eyes shall see thy textures, and thine ears shall hear a word behind thee, saying,

01:50:10.221 --> 01:50:15.461
This is the way, walk ye in it, when ye turn to the right hand and when ye turn to the left.

01:50:16.161 --> 01:50:20.921
Ye shall defile also the covering of thy graven images of silver, and the ornament of thy molten

01:50:20.921 --> 01:50:26.421
images of gold. Thou shalt cast them away as a menstrous cloth, thou shalt say unto it,

01:50:26.621 --> 01:50:31.581
Get thee hence. Then shall he give the rain of thy seed, that thou shalt sow the ground withal,

01:50:31.941 --> 01:50:36.281
and bread of the increase of the earth, and it shall be fat and plenteous. In that day shall

01:50:36.281 --> 01:50:41.381
thy cattle feed in large pastures. The oxen likewise and the young asses that ear the ground

01:50:41.381 --> 01:50:45.461
shall eat clean provender, which hath been winnowed with the shovel and with the fan.

01:50:45.961 --> 01:50:51.081
And there shall be upon every high mountain and upon every high hill rivers and streams of water

01:50:51.081 --> 01:50:56.141
in the day of the great slaughter when the towers fall. Moreover the light of the moon shall be as

01:50:56.141 --> 01:51:00.901
the light of the sun, and the light of the sun shall be sevenfold as the light of seven days,

01:51:01.161 --> 01:51:05.561
in the day that the Lord bindeth up the breach of his people and healeth the stroke of their wound.

01:51:06.421 --> 01:51:11.041
Behold the name of the Lord cometh from far burning with his anger, and the burden thereof

01:51:11.041 --> 01:51:17.101
is heavy. His lips are full of indignation and his tongue as a devouring fire, and his breath as an

01:51:17.101 --> 01:51:21.681
overflowing stream shall reach to the midst of the neck to sift the nations with the sieve of

01:51:21.681 --> 01:51:27.501
vanity, and there shall be a bridle in the jaws of the people causing them to err. Ye shall have a

01:51:27.501 --> 01:51:32.981
song as in the night when a holy solemnity is kept, and gladness of heart as when one goeth with a

01:51:32.981 --> 01:51:38.281
pipe to come into the mountain of the Lord to the mighty one of Israel. And the Lord shall cause his

01:51:38.281 --> 01:51:43.001
glorious voice to be heard, and shall show the lighting down of his arm with the indignation of

01:51:43.001 --> 01:51:48.401
his anger, and with the flame of a devouring fire with scattering and tempest and hailstones.

01:51:49.121 --> 01:51:53.181
For through the voice of the Lord shall the Assyrian be beaten down which smote with a rod,

01:51:53.701 --> 01:51:58.101
and in every place where the grounded staff shall pass which the Lord shall lay upon him,

01:51:58.321 --> 01:52:02.321
it shall be with tablets and harps, and in battles of shaking will he fight with it.

01:52:02.321 --> 01:52:08.021
For Tophet is ordained of old, yea, for the king it is prepared, he hath made it deep and large,

01:52:08.341 --> 01:52:13.441
the pile thereof is fire and much wood. The breath of the Lord, like a stream of brimstone, doth

01:52:13.441 --> 01:52:17.081
kindle it.

01:52:29.197 --> 01:52:33.477
recordings are in the public domain for more information or to volunteer please

01:52:41.177 --> 01:52:46.337
them that go down to Egypt for help and stay on horses and trust in chariots

01:52:46.337 --> 01:52:50.397
because they are many and in horsemen because they are very strong but they

01:52:50.397 --> 01:52:56.337
look not unto the Holy One of Israel neither seek the Lord yet he also is wise

01:52:56.337 --> 01:53:00.737
and will bring evil and will not call back his words but will arise against

01:53:00.737 --> 01:53:05.597
the house of the evildoers and against the help of them that work in equity now

01:53:05.597 --> 01:53:10.977
the Egyptians are men and not God and their horses flesh and not spirit when

01:53:10.977 --> 01:53:15.537
the Lord shall stretch out his hand both he that helpeth shall fall and he that

01:53:16.197 --> 01:53:21.897
down and they all shall fail together for thus have the Lord spoken unto me

01:53:22.477 --> 01:53:27.077
like as the lion and the young lion roaring on his prey when a multitude of

01:53:27.077 --> 01:53:30.897
shepherds is called forth against him he will not be afraid of their voice nor

01:53:30.897 --> 01:53:35.297
abase himself for the noise of them so shall the Lord of hosts come down to

01:53:35.297 --> 01:53:40.457
fight for Mount Zion and for the hill thereof as birds flying so will the Lord

01:53:40.457 --> 01:53:45.517
of hosts defend Jerusalem defending also he will deliver it and passing over he

01:53:45.517 --> 01:53:50.357
will preserve it turn ye unto him from whom the children of Israel have deeply

01:53:50.897 --> 01:53:55.857
revolted for in that day every man shall cast away his idols of silver and his

01:53:55.857 --> 01:54:00.877
idols of gold which your own hands have made unto you for a sin then shall the

01:54:00.877 --> 01:54:05.757
Assyrian fall with the sword not of a mighty man and the sword not of a mean

01:54:05.757 --> 01:54:10.237
man shall devour him but he shall flee from the sword and his young men shall

01:54:10.237 --> 01:54:15.237
be discomforted and he shall pass over to his stronghold for fear and his

01:54:15.237 --> 01:54:19.557
princes shall be afraid of the ensign sayeth the Lord whose fire is in Zion

01:54:19.557 --> 01:54:25.717
and his furnace in Jerusalem behold a king shall reign in

01:54:25.717 --> 01:54:30.597
righteousness and princes shall rule in judgment and a man shall be as an

01:54:30.597 --> 01:54:35.297
hiding place from the wind and a covet from the tempest as rivers of water in a

01:54:35.297 --> 01:54:40.517
dry place as the shadow of a great rock in a weary land and the eyes of them

01:54:40.517 --> 01:54:46.057
shall not be dim and the ears of them that here shall haken the heart also of

01:54:46.057 --> 01:54:49.937
the rash shall understand knowledge and the tongue of the stammerers shall be

01:54:49.937 --> 01:54:55.077
ready to speak plainly the vile person shall be no more called liberal nor the

01:54:55.077 --> 01:54:59.917
churl said to be bountiful for the vile person will speak villainy and his heart

01:54:59.917 --> 01:55:05.097
will work iniquity to practice hypocrisy and to utter error against the Lord to

01:55:05.097 --> 01:55:09.297
make empty the soul of the hungry and he will cause the drink of the thirsty to

01:55:09.297 --> 01:55:14.837
fail the instruments also of the churl are evil he deviseth wicked devices to

01:55:14.837 --> 01:55:19.857
destroy the poor with lying words even when the needy speaketh right but the

01:55:19.857 --> 01:55:25.377
liberal deviseth liberal things and by liberal things shall he stand rise up ye

01:55:25.377 --> 01:55:29.717
women that are at ease hear my voice ye careless daughters give ear unto my

01:55:29.717 --> 01:55:34.617
speech many days and years shall you be troubled ye careless women for the

01:55:34.617 --> 01:55:39.277
vintage shall fail the gathering shall not come tremble ye women that are at

01:55:39.277 --> 01:55:43.877
ease be troubled ye careless ones strip you and make you bare and gird sackcloth

01:55:43.877 --> 01:55:48.137
upon your loins they shall lament for the teats for the pleasant fields for

01:55:48.137 --> 01:55:53.297
the fruitful vine upon the land of my people shall come up thorns and briars

01:55:53.297 --> 01:55:57.997
yay upon all the houses of joy in the joyous city because the palaces shall

01:55:57.997 --> 01:56:03.157
be forsaken the multitude of the city shall be left the forts and towers shall

01:56:03.157 --> 01:56:09.017
be for dens forever a joy of wild asses a pasture of flocks until the spirit be

01:56:09.017 --> 01:56:13.517
fought upon us from on high and the wilderness be a fruitful field and the

01:56:13.517 --> 01:56:17.657
fruitful field be counted for a forest then judgment shall dwell in the

01:56:17.657 --> 01:56:21.777
wilderness and righteousness remain in the fruitful field and the work of

01:56:21.777 --> 01:56:26.117
righteousness shall be peace and the effect of righteousness quietness and

01:56:26.117 --> 01:56:31.257
assurance forever and my people shall dwell in a peaceable habitation and in

01:56:31.257 --> 01:56:35.697
shore dwellings and in quiet resting places when it shall hail coming down on

01:56:35.697 --> 01:56:40.377
the forest and the city shall be low in a low place blessed are ye that so

01:56:40.377 --> 01:56:45.017
beside all waters that send forth thither the feet of the ox and the ass

01:56:45.597 --> 01:56:50.777
woe to thee that spoilest and thou was not spoiled and dealers

01:56:50.777 --> 01:56:55.417
treacherously and they dealt not treacherously with thee when thou shalt

01:56:55.417 --> 01:56:59.997
cease to spoil thou shalt be spoiled and when thou shalt make an end to deal

01:56:59.997 --> 01:57:04.937
treacherously they shall deal treacherously with thee O Lord be gracious

01:57:04.937 --> 01:57:10.017
unto us we have waited for thee be thou their arm every morning our salvation

01:57:10.017 --> 01:57:15.517
also in the time of trouble at the noise of the tumult the people fled at the

01:57:15.517 --> 01:57:19.617
lifting up of thyself the nations were scattered and your spoil shall be

01:57:19.617 --> 01:57:23.417
gathered like the gathering of the caterpillar as the running to and fro of

01:57:23.417 --> 01:57:28.757
locusts shall he run upon them the Lord is exalted for he dwelleth on high he

01:57:28.757 --> 01:57:32.857
has filled Zion with judgment and righteousness and wisdom and knowledge

01:57:32.857 --> 01:57:37.437
shall be the stability of thy times and strength of salvation the fear of the

01:57:37.437 --> 01:57:42.617
Lord is his treasure behold their valiant ones shall cry without the

01:57:42.617 --> 01:57:47.797
ambassadors of peace shall weep bitterly the highways lie waste the wayfaring man

01:57:47.797 --> 01:57:52.837
ceaseth he hath broken the covenant he hath despised the cities he regardeth no

01:57:52.837 --> 01:57:58.677
man the earth mourneth and languisheth Lebanon is ashamed and hewn down Sharon

01:57:58.677 --> 01:58:03.657
is like a wilderness and Bashan and Carmel shake off their fruits now will I

01:58:03.657 --> 01:58:09.377
rise saith the Lord now will I be exalted now will I lift up myself ye shall

01:58:09.377 --> 01:58:14.437
conceive chaff ye shall bring forth stubble your breath as fire shall devour

01:58:14.437 --> 01:58:19.477
you and the people shall be as the burnings of lime as thorns cut up shall

01:58:19.477 --> 01:58:24.417
they be burned in the fire here ye that are far off what I have done and ye

01:58:24.417 --> 01:58:29.357
that are near acknowledge my might the sinners in Zion are afraid fearfulness

01:58:29.357 --> 01:58:33.717
hath surprised the hypocrites who among us shall dwell with the devouring fire

01:58:33.717 --> 01:58:38.277
who among us shall dwell with everlasting burnings he that walketh

01:58:38.277 --> 01:58:43.217
righteously and speaketh uprightly he that despiseth the gain of oppressions

01:58:43.217 --> 01:58:47.097
that shaketh his hands from holding of bribes that stop at his ears from

01:58:47.097 --> 01:58:52.437
hearing of blood and shut at his eyes from seeing evil he shall dwell on high

01:58:52.437 --> 01:58:56.397
his place of defense shall be the munitions of rocks bread shall be given

01:58:56.397 --> 01:59:02.417
him his waters shall be sure thine eyes shall see the king in his beauty they

01:59:02.417 --> 01:59:07.797
shall behold the land that is very far off thine heart shall meditate terror

01:59:07.797 --> 01:59:12.137
where is the scribe where is the receiver where is he that counted the

01:59:12.137 --> 01:59:16.857
towers thou shalt not see a fierce people a people of a deeper speech than

01:59:16.857 --> 01:59:21.037
thou canst perceive of a stammering tongue that thou canst not understand

01:59:21.037 --> 01:59:25.917
look upon Zion the city of our celebrities thine eyes shall see

01:59:25.917 --> 01:59:30.117
Jerusalem a quiet habitation a tabernacle that shall not be taken down

01:59:30.777 --> 01:59:35.197
not one of the stakes thereof shall ever be removed neither shall any of the

01:59:35.197 --> 01:59:39.957
cords thereof be broken but there the glorious Lord will be unto us a place

01:59:39.957 --> 01:59:44.877
of broad rivers and streams wherein shall go no galley with oars neither shall

01:59:44.877 --> 01:59:49.697
gallant ship pass thereby for the Lord is our judge the Lord is our lawgiver

01:59:49.697 --> 01:59:55.017
the Lord is our King he will save us thy tacklings are loosed they could not

01:59:55.017 --> 01:59:59.357
well strengthen their mast they could not spread the sail then is the prey of

01:59:59.357 --> 02:00:04.637
a great spoil divided the lame take the prey and the inhabitants shall not say I

02:00:04.637 --> 02:00:08.657
am sick the people that dwell therein shall be forgiven for their iniquity

02:00:19.697 --> 02:00:20.537
you

02:00:43.061 --> 02:00:43.621
34.

02:00:45.401 --> 02:00:49.141
Come near, ye nations, to hear, and hearken, ye people.

02:00:49.141 --> 02:00:51.921
Let the earth hear, and all that is therein,

02:00:52.421 --> 02:00:54.841
the world and all things that come forth of it.

02:00:55.321 --> 02:00:58.061
For the indignation of the Lord is upon all nations,

02:00:58.161 --> 02:01:00.021
and his fury upon all their armies.

02:01:00.641 --> 02:01:02.441
He hath utterly destroyed them,

02:01:02.741 --> 02:01:04.401
he hath delivered them to the slaughter.

02:01:05.521 --> 02:01:07.481
Their slain also shall be cast out,

02:01:07.681 --> 02:01:10.061
and their stink shall come up out of their carcasses,

02:01:10.481 --> 02:01:12.741
and the mountains shall be melted with their blood.

02:01:13.241 --> 02:01:15.501
And all the host of heaven shall be dissolved,

02:01:15.601 --> 02:01:18.041
and the heavens shall be rolled together as a scroll,

02:01:18.041 --> 02:01:20.201
and all their host shall fall down,

02:01:20.261 --> 02:01:22.281
as the leaf falleth off from the vine,

02:01:22.501 --> 02:01:24.561
and as a falling fig from the fig-tree.

02:01:25.521 --> 02:01:27.821
For my sword shall be bathed in heaven.

02:01:28.401 --> 02:01:30.661
Behold, it shall come down upon Idumea,

02:01:30.861 --> 02:01:33.081
and upon the people of my curse to judgment.

02:01:34.081 --> 02:01:36.141
The sword of the Lord is filled with blood.

02:01:36.581 --> 02:01:38.401
It is made fat with fatness,

02:01:38.521 --> 02:01:40.201
and with the blood of lambs and goats,

02:01:40.361 --> 02:01:42.321
with the fat of the kidneys of rams.

02:01:42.641 --> 02:01:44.841
For the Lord hath a sacrifice in Basra,

02:01:45.121 --> 02:01:47.401
and a great slaughter in the land of Idumea.

02:01:48.041 --> 02:01:50.381
And the unicorns shall come down with them,

02:01:50.461 --> 02:01:52.001
and the bullocks with the bulls,

02:01:52.221 --> 02:01:54.241
and their land shall be soaked with blood,

02:01:54.521 --> 02:01:57.201
and their dust made fat with fatness.

02:01:58.041 --> 02:02:00.261
For it is the day of the Lord's vengeance,

02:02:00.741 --> 02:02:03.841
and the year of recompenses for the controversy of Zion.

02:02:05.041 --> 02:02:07.501
And the streams thereof shall be turned into pitch,

02:02:07.761 --> 02:02:09.821
and the dust thereof into brimstone,

02:02:09.881 --> 02:02:12.521
and the land thereof shall become burning pitch.

02:02:12.781 --> 02:02:15.161
It shall not be quenched night nor day.

02:02:15.161 --> 02:02:17.521
The smoke thereof shall go up for ever,

02:02:17.561 --> 02:02:20.261
from generation to generation it shall lie waste.

02:02:20.581 --> 02:02:22.941
None shall pass through it for ever and ever.

02:02:23.561 --> 02:02:26.421
But the cormorant and the bittern shall possess it.

02:02:26.741 --> 02:02:29.701
The owl also and the raven shall dwell in it,

02:02:29.841 --> 02:02:32.581
and he shall stretch out upon it the line of confusion,

02:02:33.001 --> 02:02:34.621
and the stones of emptiness.

02:02:36.101 --> 02:02:38.581
They shall call the nobles thereof to the kingdom,

02:02:38.821 --> 02:02:40.161
but none shall be there,

02:02:40.341 --> 02:02:42.061
and all her princes shall be nothing.

02:02:42.941 --> 02:02:45.021
And thorns shall come up in her palaces,

02:02:45.161 --> 02:02:48.081
nettles and brambles in the fortresses thereof,

02:02:48.221 --> 02:02:50.481
and it shall be in habitation of dragons,

02:02:50.661 --> 02:02:52.261
and a court for owls.

02:02:53.201 --> 02:02:55.641
The wild beasts of the desert shall also meet

02:02:55.641 --> 02:02:57.201
with the wild beasts of the island,

02:02:57.361 --> 02:02:59.181
and the sadder shall cry to his fellow.

02:02:59.521 --> 02:03:01.741
The screech owl also shall rest there,

02:03:01.821 --> 02:03:03.761
and find for herself a place of rest.

02:03:05.301 --> 02:03:07.641
There shall the great owl make her nest and lay,

02:03:07.801 --> 02:03:09.761
and hatch and gather under her shadow.

02:03:10.341 --> 02:03:12.261
There shall the vultures also be gathered,

02:03:12.561 --> 02:03:13.641
every one with her mate.

02:03:15.401 --> 02:03:18.001
Seek ye out the book of the Lord, and read,

02:03:18.281 --> 02:03:20.061
No one of these shall fail.

02:03:20.621 --> 02:03:21.861
None shall want her mate.

02:03:22.281 --> 02:03:23.761
For my mouth it had commanded,

02:03:24.001 --> 02:03:25.921
and his spirit it had gathered them.

02:03:26.881 --> 02:03:28.781
And he hath cast the lot for them,

02:03:28.941 --> 02:03:31.601
and his hand hath divided it unto them by line.

02:03:32.021 --> 02:03:33.421
They shall possess it for ever.

02:03:33.621 --> 02:03:36.721
From generation to generation shall they dwell therein.

02:03:40.581 --> 02:03:43.941
The wilderness and the solitary place shall be glad for them,

02:03:43.941 --> 02:03:47.761
and the desert shall rejoice and blossom as the rose.

02:03:48.721 --> 02:03:50.201
It shall blossom abundantly,

02:03:50.381 --> 02:03:52.461
and rejoice even with joy and singing.

02:03:53.061 --> 02:03:55.621
The glory of Lebanon shall be given unto it,

02:03:55.941 --> 02:03:57.921
the excellency of Carmel and Sharon.

02:03:58.441 --> 02:04:00.201
They shall see the glory of the Lord,

02:04:00.341 --> 02:04:01.921
and the excellency of our God.

02:04:02.881 --> 02:04:04.481
Strengthen ye the weak hands,

02:04:04.761 --> 02:04:06.461
and confirm the feeble knees.

02:04:07.361 --> 02:04:09.521
Say to them that are of a fearful heart,

02:04:09.981 --> 02:04:11.501
Be strong, fear not.

02:04:11.501 --> 02:04:13.941
Behold, your God will come with vengeance,

02:04:14.381 --> 02:04:16.101
even God with a recompense.

02:04:16.341 --> 02:04:17.841
He will come and save you.

02:04:18.661 --> 02:04:20.681
Then the eyes of the blind shall be opened,

02:04:21.001 --> 02:04:23.581
and the ears of the deaf shall be unstopped.

02:04:24.061 --> 02:04:26.661
Then shall the lame man leap as in heart,

02:04:27.061 --> 02:04:28.661
and the tongue of the dumb sing.

02:04:29.841 --> 02:04:32.201
For in the wilderness shall waters break out,

02:04:32.381 --> 02:04:33.701
and streams in the desert,

02:04:34.241 --> 02:04:36.441
and the parched ground shall become a pool,

02:04:36.741 --> 02:04:39.041
and the thirsty land springs of water.

02:04:39.581 --> 02:04:41.461
In the habitations of dragons,

02:04:41.641 --> 02:04:44.561
where each lay shall be grass with reeds and rushes,

02:04:45.581 --> 02:04:48.241
and an highway shall be there, and a way,

02:04:48.821 --> 02:04:50.901
and it shall be called the way of holiness.

02:04:51.701 --> 02:04:54.041
The unclean shall not pass over it,

02:04:54.441 --> 02:04:57.161
but it shall be for those, the wayfaring men,

02:04:57.621 --> 02:05:00.141
though fools, shall not err therein.

02:05:01.041 --> 02:05:02.761
No lion shall be there,

02:05:02.941 --> 02:05:05.461
nor any ravenous beast shall go up thereon.

02:05:05.841 --> 02:05:07.421
It shall not be found there,

02:05:07.421 --> 02:05:09.741
but the redeemed shall walk there.

02:05:10.201 --> 02:05:12.341
And the ransomed of the Lord shall return,

02:05:12.801 --> 02:05:16.801
and come to Zion with songs and everlasting joy upon their heads.

02:05:17.361 --> 02:05:19.461
They shall obtain joy and gladness,

02:05:19.741 --> 02:05:21.921
and sorrow and sighing shall flee away.

02:05:25.761 --> 02:05:29.001
Now it came to pass in the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah

02:05:29.001 --> 02:05:34.081
that Sennacherib king of Assyria came up against all the defenced cities of Judah and took them.

02:05:34.081 --> 02:05:39.861
And the king of Assyria sent Rabshakei from Lachish to Jerusalem unto King Hezekiah with

02:05:39.861 --> 02:05:44.801
the great army, and he stood by the conduit of the upper pool in the highway of the Fuller's field.

02:05:45.721 --> 02:05:50.381
Then came forth unto him Eliakim, Hilkiah's son, which was over the house,

02:05:50.761 --> 02:05:54.661
and Shebna the scribe, and Joah, Asaph's son, the recorder.

02:05:55.721 --> 02:05:57.641
And Rabshakei said unto them,

02:05:58.301 --> 02:05:59.681
Say ye now to Hezekiah.

02:06:00.481 --> 02:06:03.081
Thus saith the great king, the king of Assyria.

02:06:03.081 --> 02:06:06.301
What confidence is this wherein thou trustest?

02:06:07.281 --> 02:06:10.541
I say, sayest thou, but they are but vain words.

02:06:10.961 --> 02:06:13.041
I have counsel and strength for war.

02:06:13.741 --> 02:06:17.261
Now on whom dost thou trust, that thou rebellest against me?

02:06:18.121 --> 02:06:22.141
Lo, thou trustest in the staff of this broken reed on Egypt,

02:06:22.661 --> 02:06:26.121
whereon if a man lean it will go into his hand and pierce it.

02:06:26.361 --> 02:06:29.321
So is Pharaoh king of Egypt to all that trust in him.

02:06:29.881 --> 02:06:33.801
But if thou say to me, We trust in the Lord our God,

02:06:34.341 --> 02:06:38.421
is it not he whose high places and whose altars Hezekiah hath taken away,

02:06:38.761 --> 02:06:42.221
and said to Judah and to Jerusalem, Ye shall worship before this altar?

02:06:43.281 --> 02:06:47.441
Now therefore give privileges, I pray thee, to my master the king of Assyria,

02:06:47.701 --> 02:06:52.661
and I will give thee two thousand horses, if thou be able on thy part to set riders upon them.

02:06:53.201 --> 02:06:57.661
How then wilt thou turn away the face of one captain of the least of my master's servant,

02:06:57.661 --> 02:07:00.741
and put thy trust on Egypt for chariots and for horsemen?

02:07:01.481 --> 02:07:04.761
And am I now come up without the Lord against this land to destroy it?

02:07:05.021 --> 02:07:08.301
The Lord said unto me, Go up against this land and destroy it.

02:07:09.661 --> 02:07:13.141
Then said Eliakim and Shebna and Joah unto Rabshakei,

02:07:13.641 --> 02:07:17.741
Speak, I pray thee, unto thy servants in the Syrian language, for we understand it,

02:07:17.981 --> 02:07:21.881
and speak not to us in the Jews' language in the ears of the people that are on the wall.

02:07:23.081 --> 02:07:28.541
But Rabshakei said, Hath my master sent me to thy master and to thee to speak these words?

02:07:28.841 --> 02:07:32.841
Hath he not sent me to the men that sit upon the wall that they may eat their own dung

02:07:32.841 --> 02:07:38.001
and drink their own piss with you? Then Rabshakei stood, and cried with a loud

02:07:38.001 --> 02:07:43.361
voice in the Jews' language, and said, Hear ye the words of the great king, the king of Assyria.

02:07:44.381 --> 02:07:49.681
Thus saith the king, Let not Hezekiah deceive you, for he shall not be able to deliver you.

02:07:49.681 --> 02:07:54.561
Neither let Hezekiah make you trust in the Lord, saying, The Lord will surely deliver us.

02:07:54.761 --> 02:07:58.201
This city shall not be delivered into the hand of the king of Assyria.

02:07:59.821 --> 02:08:02.981
Harken not to Hezekiah, for thus saith the king of Assyria,

02:08:03.441 --> 02:08:06.561
Make an agreement with me by a present, and come out to me,

02:08:06.781 --> 02:08:10.701
And eat ye every one of his vine and every one of his fig tree,

02:08:10.861 --> 02:08:13.381
And drink ye every one the waters of his own cistern,

02:08:14.201 --> 02:08:17.361
Until I come and take you away to a land like your own land,

02:08:17.361 --> 02:08:20.721
A land of corn and wine, a land of bread and vineyards.

02:08:22.821 --> 02:08:26.621
Beware lest Hezekiah persuade you, saying, The Lord will deliver us.

02:08:26.901 --> 02:08:30.761
Hath any of the gods of the nations delivered his land out of the hand of the king of Assyria?

02:08:31.441 --> 02:08:35.941
Where are the gods of Hamath and Arphad? Where are the gods of Seferveim?

02:08:36.361 --> 02:08:38.701
And have they delivered Samaria out of my hand?

02:08:39.581 --> 02:08:44.101
Who are they among all the gods of these lands that have delivered their land out of my hand,

02:08:44.101 --> 02:08:46.741
That the Lord should deliver Jerusalem out of my hand?

02:08:47.841 --> 02:08:50.881
But they held their peace, and answered him not a word,

02:08:51.241 --> 02:08:54.721
For the king's commandment was, saying, Answer him not.

02:08:55.661 --> 02:08:59.281
Then came Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, that was over the household,

02:08:59.501 --> 02:09:02.821
And Shebna the scribe, and Joah the son of Asaph the recorder,

02:09:03.021 --> 02:09:06.901
To Hezekiah with their clothes rent, and told him the words of Rabshakei.

02:09:21.340 --> 02:09:23.260
OF THE BOOK OF ISAIAH

